 the United States during its publication. The magazine had a wide readership, with a circulation of over three million by the late 1940s.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'This Week was also highly respected in the publishing industry for its comprehensive news coverage, high editorial standards, and iconic cover art.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'This Week magazine ceased publication in 1969, after a 34-year run. The magazine was a landmark in the history of American journalism, and its influence is still felt in the publishing industry today.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'This Week''s legacy is reflected in the numerous publications that followed in its footsteps, including Time, Newsweek, and U.S. News & World Report. The magazine is also remembered for its iconic cover art, which is still revered by collectors and designers today.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

