VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A teen magazine focused on celebrity gossip, pop culture, fashion, and beauty, providing exclusive interviews and engaging content for teenage girls.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Twist is a teen magazine that was first published in 1997. The magazine is primarily focused on celebrity gossip and pop culture, and it has gained a large readership among teenage girls.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Twist was first published in January 1997 by Monarch Services, a division of Primedia. The magazine was originally known as Big Twist, and it was focused on general entertainment news and other topics of interest to teenagers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over time, Twist shifted its focus more towards celebrity gossip and pop culture, and the magazine began to attract a large readership among teenage girls. In 2003, Twist was acquired by Bauer Media Group, which is based in Germany.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since then, Twist has continued to publish an array of content related to celebrity gossip and teen pop culture, including articles on the latest fashion trends, beauty tips and advice, and exclusive interviews with popular entertainers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Twist is primarily focused on celebrity gossip and pop culture, and it provides readers with a wide range of content related to these topics. The magazine regularly features exclusive interviews with popular entertainers, as well as articles on the latest fashion trends, beauty tips and advice, and other topics of interest to teenage girls.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its celebrity-focused content, Twist also features quizzes, puzzles, and other interactive features designed to engage and entertain its readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Editors and Contributors' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Twist has been edited by a number of well-known figures in the teen magazine industry over the years. Current editor-in-chief Brittany Galla has been with the magazine since 2016, and has helped to guide its continued success.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Contributors to Twist over the years have included many well-known writers and journalists, as well as teen bloggers and influencers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Impact and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since its launch in 1997, Twist has become one of the most popular teen magazines in the United States, and it has gained a large readership among teenage girls. The magazine''s focus on celebrity gossip and pop culture has resonated with its target audience, and it has helped to shape the way that many young people think about these topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although Twist faces considerable competition in today''s crowded media landscape, the magazine remains an important part of the teen magazine market, and it continues to offer valuable content and insights to its readers.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Skate Rider
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Skate Rider', N'skate-rider', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American skateboarding magazine (mid-1970s to early 1980s), providing news, product reviews, professional interviews, and skate photography.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Skate Rider was an American skateboarding magazine published in the period of mid-1970s to early 1980s, providing a comprehensive look into the world of skateboarding during its golden era.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The content of Skate Rider was an eclectic mix of skateboarding news, product reviews, interviews with professional skateboarders, and in-depth features on skateboarding tricks, techniques and skateboard culture. It became famous for its high-quality photography that showcased the dynamism and creativity within the sport, alongside instructional articles aimed at both novice and advanced skateboarders.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Due to the boom in popularity of skateboarding in the 1970s, Skate Rider was launched as a source of information and a means of connection for the rapidly growing skateboarding community. Its colorful and striking covers, featuring iconic images of skateboarders in action, became its unique signature. Despite its prevalent success in the skating community, the magazine had a relatively short run due to the decline in popularity of skateboarding in the early 1980s.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Skateboard Mag
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Skateboard Mag', N'the-skateboard-mag', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American monthly skateboarding magazine (2004-2017) focusing on skateboarding culture, gear, events, and professional skateboarder features.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Skateboard Mag was a monthly American skateboarding magazine, published from 2004 to 2017. It was established by a group of professional skateboarders and industry leaders looking to create a different type of skateboarding publication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Skateboard Mag provided extensive coverage of the global skateboarding scene. It included features on professional skateboarders, detailed articles on skateboarding gear and equipment, skate park reviews, and event coverage. The magazine was known for its high-quality photography that captured the athleticism and artistry of skateboarding. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Skateboard Mag was founded by a team of renowned figures from the skateboarding industry, including professional skateboarders Steve Berra and Eric Koston, industry stalwart Mike Mihaly, and legendary skateboard photographers Atiba Jefferson and Dave Swift. The main goal was to present skateboarding in its purest form and the team emphasized authenticity and passion over commercial interests.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2016, the magazine was acquired by Dwindle Distribution but continued to operate under its distinct brand. Unfortunately, due to changing industry dynamics and a shift to digital media, The Skateboard Mag ceased publication in 2017. However, it left a legacy of pushing skateboarding media forward and captivated a generation with its genuine depiction of the sport.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Skateboarder
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Skateboarder', N'skateboarder', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription First-ever skateboarding magazine (1964-2013), featuring industry updates, professional interviews, gear reviews, and skate photography.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Skateboarder was a United States-based magazine on skateboarding that was first published in 1964, making it the first ever skateboarding magazine. It served as the premier platform for skateboarding culture and news for over four decades.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Skateboarder magazine''s content featured a wide scope of skateboarding coverage. Apart from delivering news and updates from the skateboarding scene, it featured interviews with both prominent and upcoming skateboarders, showcased new skateboarding techniques and offered in-depth reviews of skateboarding gear. The magazine also gained much acclaim for its high-quality photography, capturing the energy and creativity of the sport and the skaters.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Skateboarder magazine was initially released as a quarterly publication in Winter 1964 under the title "The Quarterly Skateboarder", but quickly rebranded as "Skateboarder" by its second issue in Spring 1965. The magazine was initially produced by Surfer Publications out of Dana Point, California, and was created as a spin-off to Surfer Magazine. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Regardless of two early downfalls when the skateboarding industry faced recessions in the late 60s and early 80s, the magazine nevertheless made a triumphant return and ultimately became a monthly publication. In 2013, after a long and successful run as a print magazine, Skateboarder switched to an all-digital format. However, it ceased publication altogether later that same year - marking the end of an era.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

