VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American magazine focused on fashion, beauty, and culture for teenage girls.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Teen Vogue is an American magazine that targets teenage girls and covers fashion, beauty, and culture. It is a monthly publication that was first published in 2003.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Teen Vogue was created as a spin-off of the popular fashion magazine Vogue. The first issue was published in February 2003. At the time, the magazine''s editor-in-chief was Amy Astley, who had previously worked for Vogue.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'From the beginning, Teen Vogue was known for its sophisticated approach to teenage fashion and beauty, and its focus on social and cultural issues that were important to teenage girls. Over the years, the magazine has been a trendsetter in youth culture and has helped to launch the careers of several prominent young women, including Lena Dunham and Karlie Kloss.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2016, the magazine made headlines when it published an editorial condemning then-presidential candidate Donald Trump''s proposed policies on immigration and other issues. The editorial caused controversy and garnered attention from media outlets around the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Teen Vogue covers a range of topics, including fashion, beauty, politics, and social issues. The magazine is known for its mix of high fashion and streetwear, and for its focus on promoting positive body image and self-esteem among its readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to fashion and beauty features, Teen Vogue also covers cultural events, music, and entertainment. The magazine has been praised for its coverage of social and political issues, including women''s rights, LGBTQ+ issues, and sexual assault.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Impact and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since its launch in 2003, Teen Vogue has become a major force in the publishing industry, and an important voice for teenage girls. The magazine''s focus on fashion, beauty, and culture has helped to shape the tastes and attitudes of several generations of young women.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its impact on the publishing industry, Teen Vogue has also been a cultural touchstone, influencing the language, trends, and social norms of teenage girls around the world.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- TeenSet
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'TeenSet', N'teenset', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Defunct American magazine of the 1960s focused on music, fashion, and pop culture for teenagers.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'TeenSet was an American magazine that targeted teenage readers and covered fashion, music, movies and other youth culture topics. It was a monthly publication that was published from 1965 until 1970.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'TeenSet was launched in 1965 by Hillman Periodicals, a New York-based publishing company. The first issue featured the Beatles on its cover, and the magazine quickly became known for its coverage of music and pop culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to feature articles on major music acts of the time, such as the Beatles, the Rolling Stones, and the Beach Boys, TeenSet also featured regular columns on fashion, movies, and television.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was known for its colorful, eye-catching covers, which often featured photographs of popular musicians and actors.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content and Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'TeenSet was primarily focused on music and pop culture, and many of its articles and columns were devoted to artists and their work. The magazine also covered fashion, and regularly featured fashion spreads and style tips.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition, TeenSet had regular columns on teen health, advice, and lifestyles. The magazine was designed to appeal to a broad range of teenagers, covering a wide variety of topics and interests.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Impact and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although TeenSet only published for a short time, its legacy can still be felt today. The magazine helped to define youth culture in the late 1960s, and was one of the first publications to focus exclusively on popular music.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'TeenSet was also an important platform for many emerging writers and photographers, some of whom went on to become major figures in their respective fields.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, TeenSet is remembered as an important document of the music and fashion of the era, and continues to be an influence on contemporary youth culture.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Prosper Magazine
