VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A now-defunct technology industry publication that rose to prominence during the dot-com boom and bust.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Industry Standard was a weekly magazine that covered the technology industry during the dot-com boom and bust of the late 1990s and early 2000s.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Industry Standard was founded in 1998 by John Battelle, and quickly became a leading voice in the tech industry. The magazine was based in San Francisco, California, and covered technology news and trends from Silicon Valley and beyond.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'At the height of the dot-com boom, The Industry Standard became a symbol of the tech economy''s excesses. The magazine was known for its lavish parties and extravagant spending. However, as the tech bubble burst, The Industry Standard''s fortunes began to decline.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2001, The Industry Standard ceased publication, citing financial difficulties.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Industry Standard covered a wide range of topics related to the technology industry. The magazine featured articles on emerging trends and technologies, as well as profiles of industry figures and analysis of market trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was known for its in-depth reporting and analysis of the tech industry. It was also praised for its design and layout, which was considered innovative for its time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Audience and Reception' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Industry Standard had a devoted readership in the tech industry and was widely respected for its reporting and analysis. The magazine received numerous awards for journalism and design, including a National Magazine Award in 2000 for General Excellence.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'However, The Industry Standard also faced criticism for its role in promoting the dot-com bubble. The magazine was accused of glossing over the risks and challenges facing the industry, and of contributing to an atmosphere of hype and speculation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively short run, The Industry Standard had a significant impact on the technology industry. The magazine helped to define the culture of Silicon Valley during the dot-com era, and its coverage of emerging technologies and trends was influential in shaping the direction of the industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, The Industry Standard is remembered as a symbol of the dot-com era, and its legacy serves as a cautionary tale about the risks of hype and speculation in the technology industry.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Indy Men's Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Indy Men''s Magazine', N'indy-mens-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A lifestyle magazine for men focusing on fashion, style, health, fitness, and entertainment, founded in 1999 and ceased publication in 2009 due to the decline of print media and the effects of the Great Recession.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Indy Men''s Magazine, also known as Independent Men''s Magazine, was a lifestyle publication in the United States. It catered to men and covered topics such as fashion, style, health, fitness, and entertainment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Indy Men was founded in 1999 by Mark A. Zappa in Tampa, Florida. It was initially launched as a regional magazine focused on the Tampa Bay area, but later expanded to cover a broader audience.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Indy Men showcased exclusive interviews from prominent figures, including actors, musicians, and other celebrities. The magazine also covered local events, reviews on latest gadgets, and sports activities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2009, due to the decline of print media and the effects of the Great Recession, Indy Men ceased publication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Indy Men Magazine was targeted at the modern man who was looking for an independent and resourceful outlook towards life. The publication featured profiles of successful businessmen and entrepreneurs, along with articles on cars, technology, and travel.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Indy Men also featured interviews with musicians, athletes, actors, and other prominent figures. The magazine had numerous columns, including "The Rules," which offered tips on fashion and style, and "Man Cave," which covered the latest in gear and gadgets.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Audience and Reception' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Indy Men had a relatively small readership but was respected for its focus on men''s lifestyle topics. The magazine''s distinctive voice and unique content helped it stand out in a crowded market.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'However, Indy Men faced challenges competing with larger, more established men''s publications like Maxim and GQ. The magazine''s decline and eventual closure were one of many casualties of the print media industry''s upheaval in the 2000s and 2010s.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Indy Men magazine was a unique and independent voice in the men''s publishing world. Its focus on lifestyle topics and interviews with prominent figures set it apart from its competitors.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, Indy Men is remembered as a publication that challenged traditional notions of masculinity and provided a fresh perspective on what it meant to be a modern man in the twenty-first century.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- InformationWeek
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'InformationWeek', N'informationweek', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A weekly magazine and online publication that focused on information technology news, analysis, and research, including software, hardware, security, cloud computing, mobile devices, and industry trends.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'InformationWeek was a weekly print and online magazine in the United States that focused on information technology (IT). It provided news, analysis, and research on various topics related to IT, including software, hardware, security, cloud computing, mobile devices, and industry trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'InformationWeek was founded in 1985 by CMP Media, a company that specializes in media and marketing. It was first published in print as a bi-weekly magazine and later shifted to a weekly publication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, InformationWeek launched a website in 1995 to complement its print publication and provide content to its growing readership. The website provided news, blogs, interactive features, and whitepapers on various IT topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2013, InformationWeek merged with CRN, an IT industry magazine, to form CRN Tech. The InformationWeek website was retained as a separate site under the CRN Tech umbrella.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'InformationWeek provided its readers with a mix of news, analysis, and research on IT topics. The publication covered a wide range of issues related to software, hardware, security, cloud computing, mobile devices, and industry trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also featured articles on best practices for businesses, including strategies for managing IT projects and advice on how to maximize the return on investment (ROI) of IT initiatives.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'InformationWeek was known for its annual ranking of the top 500 technology companies in the United States, as well as its InformationWeek 500 award, which recognized the most innovative users of IT.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Audience and Reception' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'InformationWeek had a large readership among IT professionals, including CIOs, CTOs, and other IT executives and managers. The magazine was respected in the industry for its comprehensive coverage of IT topics and its focus on providing practical guidance and strategic advice to its readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, InformationWeek received numerous awards for its content, including the Neal award, which recognizes excellence in business journalism, and the Webby award, which honors excellence on the internet.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'InformationWeek was a significant player in the IT industry for over three decades. Its comprehensive coverage of IT topics and its focus on providing strategic advice and practical guidance to its readers helped it become a trusted resource for IT professionals.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Today, InformationWeek is remembered as a publication that helped shape the IT industry and provided insights and guidance to its readers on how to leverage technology to support their businesses.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

