VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A fanzine dedicated to Marvel Comics and related media that played a significant role in the growth of comic book fandom in the 1960s.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Marvelmania International was a fanzine dedicated to Marvel Comics and related media that was published in the 1960s. The magazine was first published in 1967 by Marvel Comics and is widely considered one of the earliest and most influential fanzines in comic book history.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Marvelmania International was edited by famed comic book artist and writer Rick Jones, and featured contributions from many other notable comic book creators and fans. The magazine included articles, interviews, reviews, and art related to Marvel Comics and its characters.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the highlights of Marvelmania International was its fan fiction, which allowed readers to submit their own stories featuring Marvel Comics characters. The magazine also included fan art, contests, and other fan-focused content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its popularity among Marvel Comics fans, Marvelmania International only lasted a few issues before being cancelled in 1969 due to financial difficulties. However, its legacy has lived on, with many comic book historians citing its influence on the growth of comic book fandom in the 1960s and beyond.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Marvelmania International remains highly sought after by collectors, with original issues fetching high prices at auctions and comic book conventions. The magazine is a testament to the passion and creativity of comic book fans, and to the enduring popularity of Marvel Comics and its iconic characters.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

