VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A bimonthly magazine providing news, reviews, and features on model rocketry, including rocket design and safety tips.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Model Rocketry is a bimonthly magazine that focuses on the hobby and sport of model rocketry. The magazine was first published in 1971 and is published by the National Association of Rocketry (NAR).' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Model Rocketry provides its readers with news, reviews, and features on the latest developments in the field of model rocketry. The magazine covers topics such as rocket design, construction, and launch techniques, as well as model rocket safety and regulations. It also includes articles on the latest rocketry events and competitions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is aimed at both beginners and experienced model rocket enthusiasts. Model Rocketry''s articles are written by experts in the field, including hobbyists, engineers, and scientists.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, Model Rocketry also operates a website, which includes digital versions of the magazine''s articles, an online store for rocketry supplies and tools, and a community forum for rocket enthusiasts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The National Association of Rocketry, which publishes Model Rocketry, is a non-profit organization that promotes the safe and educational use of model rockets. The NAR also organizes rocketry events and competitions, provides educational resources for hobbyists and educators, and advocates for the hobby on a national level.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Modern Electrics
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Modern Electrics', N'modern-electrics', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine providing news, reviews, and features on the latest developments in the field of amateur radio technology.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electrics was a monthly magazine published in the United States between 1908 and 1913. It was one of the first magazines devoted to amateur radio, a hobby that was then in its infancy.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electrics provided its readers with news, reviews, and features on the latest developments in the field of radio technology, including wireless telegraphy and long-distance communication. The magazine also offered technical diagrams and instructions for enthusiasts looking to build their own radio equipment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was one of the first publications to feature the work of Nikola Tesla, a Serbian-American inventor and engineer known for his contributions to the development of the modern alternating current (AC) electrical system. Modern Electrics published several of Tesla''s articles, including his treatise on the use of high-frequency currents in wireless communication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electrics was published by the Electro Importing Company, a mail-order company that sold radio equipment and supplies to hobbyists and professionals. The magazine was edited by Hugo Gernsback, a Luxembourgian-American inventor and science fiction writer who later became known as the "father of science fiction."' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was succeeded in 1913 by Electrical Experimenter, a publication also edited by Gernsback. Electrical Experimenter continued to cover the latest developments in radio technology, as well as other fields such as aviation and robotics. Electrical Experimenter was later renamed Science and Invention, and ceased publication in 1931.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Modern Electronics
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Modern Electronics', N'modern-electronics', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine providing practical applications and news on the latest developments in the field of electronic devices and systems.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electronics was a monthly magazine published in the United States between 1984 and 1991. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered the latest developments in electronic technology, with a focus on practical applications of electronic devices and systems. It included articles on computer hardware and software, audio and video technology, and electronic design and construction.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electronics was published by Gernsback Publications, Inc., which was founded by Hugo Gernsback, a Luxembourgian-American inventor and science fiction writer. Gernsback was known for his pioneering work in the field of science fiction, and he is credited with coining the term "science fiction" in 1929.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electronics was the successor to Electronics World, another magazine founded by Hugo Gernsback. After Modern Electronics ceased publication in 1991, it was succeeded by Electronics Now, a magazine that covered similar topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Modern Electronics featured articles from prominent engineers and designers in the electronics field, such as Forrest M. Mims III, a popular electronics author and inventor, and Robert Pease, a notable analog circuit designer. The magazine also included a "Reader Input" section, where readers could write in with questions and comments.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Though no longer in publication, Modern Electronics remains a valuable resource for those interested in the history of electronics technology.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

