VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An American dance and lifestyle magazine founded in 2004 that showcased emerging talent, diversity, and artistry in various dance genres until 2010.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Movmnt (stylized as "MOVmnt") was an American dance and lifestyle magazine that was first published in 2004 and continued until 2010. It was founded by Ivan Kane and Nadine Rajabi and aimed to highlight the diversity and artistry of dance, as well as provide insight into the culture and lifestyle surrounding it.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The publication featured articles, interviews, and photographic spreads covering a variety of dance genres, including ballet, modern, hip-hop, and tap. It also delved into dance history, social issues, and wellness, including nutrition and fitness advice specifically tailored to dancers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Movmnt was known for its commitment to showcasing emerging talent and its focus on diversity and inclusivity in the dance world. The magazine was also noted for its high-quality production values, with striking photographs and stylish design that reflected its emphasis on aesthetics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its popularity and critical acclaim within the dance community, Movmnt ceased publication in 2010 due to financial difficulties. Nevertheless, the magazine left a lasting impact on the dance world, having provided a platform for artists and fostering a strong community of dancers and dance enthusiasts.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

