VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An American trade publication focused on the multifamily housing industry, providing insights, news, and analysis on emerging technologies and trends.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Multi-Housing News (MHM) is an American trade publication that was founded in 1968 and is owned by Yardi Systems Inc. It focuses on the multifamily housing industry, providing news, analysis, and insights on trends, best practices, and emerging technologies.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The publication covers a broad range of topics, including property management, development, financing, architecture, design, and technology. It also delivers in-depth coverage of major industry events and conferences, including the National Multifamily Housing Council''s Annual Meeting and the National Apartment Association''s Education Conference and Exposition.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Multi-Housing News has a reputation for its authoritative coverage of the multifamily housing industry, and is widely considered a must-read for industry professionals. Its audience includes apartment owners, developers, property managers, investors, lenders, and other stakeholders in the multifamily housing sector.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publication, Multi-Housing News also offers digital content, including a website, e-newsletters, and webinars. It has won numerous awards for its journalism and design, including awards from the American Society of Business Publication Editors, the Society of Professional Journalists, and the National Association of Real Estate Editors.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Multinational Monitor
