VALUES ( N'National Geographic Adventure', N'national-geographic-adventure', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A magazine focused on outdoor recreation, exploration, and adventure travel, winning numerous awards for high-quality journalism and photography, even having articles on conservation efforts and sustainable tourism practices, until it ceased publication in 2009 due to financial challenges.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Geographic Adventure was a magazine that focused on outdoor recreation, exploration, and adventure travel. The publication was founded in 1999, and had a total of 78 issues before it ceased publication in 2009.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a wide range of topics related to adventure travel, including hiking, kayaking, surfing, and mountaineering. It provided readers with advice and tips on how to best experience the great outdoors, as well as recommendations for adventure travel destinations around the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Geographic Adventure was known for its high-quality journalism and photography. The magazine won numerous awards, including seven National Magazine Awards from the American Society of Magazine Editors. It was also praised for its commitment to environmental issues, and frequently featured articles on conservation efforts and sustainable tourism practices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its success, National Geographic Adventure faced financial challenges in the late 2000s, as advertisers began to pull their support due to the economic downturn. The magazine struggled to maintain profitability, and ceased publication in December 2009. However, the brand continues to live on as National Geographic Adventure Books, which publishes adventure-themed books and guides.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- National Geographic Traveler
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'National Geographic Traveler', N'national-geographic-traveler', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A magazine focused on travel and cultural exploration, with high-quality journalism and photography, award-winning travel writing and photography, responsible and sustainable travel features, and socially conscious content, with a strong online presence and guidebook series, since 1984.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Geographic Traveler is a magazine that focuses on travel and cultural exploration. The publication was founded in 1984, and is published eight times a year.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covers a wide range of topics related to leisure travel and cultural exploration, including recommendations for travel destinations and adventures, culinary experiences, and cultural events around the world. National Geographic Traveler is known for its high-quality journalism and photography, and has won numerous awards for its travel writing and photography, including four National Magazine Awards from the American Society of Magazine Editors.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its print publications, National Geographic Traveler has a strong online presence, featuring updated travel-related news and features, travel guides, and an active social media presence. The magazine also produces a series of guidebooks focused on different destinations and travel themes.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Geographic Traveler has a strong commitment to responsible and sustainable travel, and frequently features articles on eco-tourism, cultural preservation, and other ethical travel topics. The magazine also has a reputation for being socially conscious, and frequently features stories on social issues and activism around the globe.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its history, National Geographic Traveler has been a respected and influential voice in the travel industry. It ceased publication in 2019.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- National Lampoon
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'National Lampoon', N'national-lampoon', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A humor magazine founded in 1970, known for its irreverent sense of humor, satirical articles, parodies, and iconic cover illustrations, and eventually expanded to include movies, including ''Animal House,'' ''Vacation,'' and ''Christmas Vacation,'' until its financial struggles led to its closure in 1998.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Lampoon was an American humor magazine that was founded in 1970. The publication was initially a spinoff of the Harvard Lampoon, a humor magazine that was founded in 1876 at Harvard University.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was known for its irreverent sense of humor and featured satirical articles, parodies, and comics that often pushed the boundaries of good taste. It was also known for its iconic cover illustrations, many of which were created by artists like John Belushi.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Lampoon was a cultural phenomenon in the 1970s, and its brand quickly expanded beyond the magazine to include comedy albums, live shows, and eventually movies. Some of the most famous movies produced under the National Lampoon brand include Animal House, Vacation, and Christmas Vacation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its initial success, National Lampoon faced financial challenges in the 1980s. The magazine struggled to stay relevant as the comedy landscape changed, and advertisers began to pull their support due to controversial content. In 1998, the magazine folded after 28 years of publication.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its relatively short run, National Lampoon left a lasting impact on American culture, influencing a generation of comedians and satirists. Its legacy lives on in the National Lampoon radio hour, the National Lampoon Comedy Hour, and various iterations of the Vacation movie franchise.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- National Police Gazette
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'National Police Gazette', N'national-police-gazette', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An American magazine that ran for over 130 years since its founding in 1845. Known for its sensational reporting, it evolved from crime and criminal investigations to sports, entertainment, politics, and general interest topics, and helped to popularize boxing in the US.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'National Police Gazette was an American magazine that was first published in 1845, making it one of the oldest magazines in the United States. The magazine was initially focused on crime and criminal investigations, but over time evolved to include sports, entertainment, politics, and other topics of general interest.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The National Police Gazette was known for its sensationalized reporting, exaggerated stories, and racy illustrations. The magazine featured stories on everything from notorious criminals and unsolved murders to scandals in high society and the sexual exploits of celebrities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was also known for its sports coverage, and was one of the first publications to cover boxing in detail. It published scores, rankings, and analysis of the sport, and helped to popularize boxing in the United States.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'At its peak, the National Police Gazette had a circulation of over one million, making it one of the most widely read magazines in the country. However, by the mid-20th century, the magazine faced increased competition from other publications and declining interest in its sensationalist style of journalism. It ceased publication in 1977, after over 130 years of circulation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its controversial reputation, the National Police Gazette played an important role in American journalism and popular culture. Its influence can be seen in the development of modern tabloid journalism, as well as in the enduring popularity of sports like boxing.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Nautilus
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Nautilus', N'the-nautilus', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription An online science magazine offering accessible yet rigorous articles on diverse topics in science and technology, committed to promoting diversity and inclusivity in the scientific community.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nautilus is a science magazine that was first published in 2007. It is an online publication that covers a wide range of topics related to science, including biology, physics, astronomy, and technology.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was founded by science journalists Tanya Lewis and Christopher Intagliata, with the aim of providing a platform for science communication that goes beyond academic papers and conferences. The Nautilus publishes articles that are accessible to a general audience, while still maintaining scientific accuracy and rigor.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nautilus has won several awards for its science journalism, including the AAAS Kavli Science Journalism Award and the National Academy of Sciences Communication Award. The magazine has also been recognized for its design, which is interactive and visually engaging.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nautilus features articles that are written by a combination of staff writers and freelance science journalists. The magazine also partners with scientists and research institutions to bring insights from the scientific community to the wider public.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Nautilus is committed to promoting diversity and inclusivity in science, and has written extensively about the challenges faced by underrepresented groups in the scientific community. The magazine also provides a platform for scientists from different backgrounds to share their research and perspectives.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Overall, The Nautilus is a respected and influential science magazine that is dedicated to making science accessible and engaging for a wide audience.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Negro Digest
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Negro Digest', N'negro-digest', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription African American magazine publishing positive news and opinions, founded in 1942 and later renamed as Black World, influential in African American culture and politics until 1976.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Negro Digest, later renamed Black World, was a magazine aimed at African Americans that focused on culture, news, and opinions. It was published continuously from 1942 to 1976 by the Johnson Publishing Company, founded by John H. Johnson. Negro Digest''s aim was to present a positive image of African Americans to a wider audience and its articles covered many topics such as literature, music, history, and civil rights. The magazine was a platform for African American writers and intellectuals, many of whom later became major Civil Rights Movement figures.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 1961, Negro Digest was renamed Black World when its focus shifted to reflecting political and social issues affecting African Americans. Black World became more confrontational and outspoken under its new name, addressing issues such as institutional racism, police brutality, and the Vietnam War.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Negro Digest/Black World had a significant influence on African American politics and culture. Known figures such as Martin Luther King Jr., Langston Hughes, and James Baldwin all contributed to the magazine. The magazine''s contributions to African American discourse and culture can be seen in the many publications inspired by its legacy.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Nerve
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Nerve', N'nerve', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Online magazine focusing on sex and relationships, later expanding to cover broader issues in culture, politics, and technology. Ceased operations in 2017.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nerve was an online magazine founded in 1997 by Rufus Griscom and Genevieve Field in New York City. The magazine originally focused on sex and relationships, with a humorous and irreverent tone. Its articles covered various topics related to sex and love, including personal essays, interviews, and sex advice columns. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over time, the magazine expanded its focus to include commentary on broader issues related to culture, politics, and technology. Nerve also published a number of books, including the anthology, "The Best of Nerve.com". ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2008, the magazine was sold to BermanBraun, a media company founded by former Yahoo! executives, and later to IAC, a conglomerate that also owns other online media outlets like Vimeo and The Daily Beast. Following the acquisition, Nerve underwent a significant redesign and relaunched in 2009 as a more diverse and mainstream publication. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine continued to publish content until 2017 when it ceased operations after almost 20 years of operation. In its time, Nerve published work from a wide range of writers, including notable names such as Dan Savage, Roxane Gay, and Chuck Klosterman.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Nest
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Nest', N'nest', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Quarterly design publication known for unconventional explorations of design, presenting unique interiors and objects, ceased publication in 2004.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nest magazine was a quarterly design publication founded in 1997 by Joseph Holtzman in New York City. It was known for its engaging and unconventional exploration of design, presenting unusual, often overlooked objects and interiors. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s presentation was as much a part of its appeal as its content. Each issue was distinctly designed, incorporating unusual layouts and typography, as well as unique printing techniques. The magazine''s pages were often interspersed with works of art and photography that complemented the featured designs. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nest built a loyal following, with content covering a wide range of design topics including furniture, architecture, and decorative arts. Its focus was often on the unusual and unexpected, showcasing design inspiration from around the world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite critical acclaim, the magazine struggled financially over the years. After a string of financial setbacks, Nest was forced to cease publication after its Fall 2004 issue. Its editorial archives were later acquired by the Cooper Hewitt, Smithsonian Design Museum in New York City.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Nest''s legacy can be seen in the numerous design publications that followed it, as well as in the work of designers, architects and artists that were featured in its pages.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The New Armenia
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The New Armenia', N'the-new-armenia', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Armenian-American monthly publication founded in 1918 in Boston aimed to provide information and discussion platform for Armenian-Americans. Final issue published in 2000.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The New Armenia magazine was an Armenian-American monthly publication founded in 1918 in Boston, Massachusetts, USA. The magazine was created to serve as a source of information and a platform for discussion for Armenian-Americans. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine covered a wide range of topics, including politics, history, literature, and culture. Its content was often written in both Armenian and English to ensure readers of both languages could access the information. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The New Armenia played an important role in promoting Armenian-American culture and identity, as well as advocating for Armenian Genocide recognition, a major issue for the Armenian community. The magazine also supported the Armenian Revolutionary Federation, a political party focused on gaining independence for Armenia and the Armenian people.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its history, The New Armenia faced significant financial challenges. The magazine suspended production from 1921-1923 due to financial difficulties, and faced numerous other periods of struggle over the years. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite these challenges, The New Armenia remained in publication for over 80 years. The magazine''s final issue was published in the year 2000. Today, The New Armenia is remembered as an important voice for the Armenian-American community and a cultural landmark.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The New Electric Railway Journal
