VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly Christian lifestyle magazine for men, offering practical advice on faith, family, career, and health; published from 1986 to 2007.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'New Man was a monthly Christian lifestyle magazine for men, originally published from 1986 to 2007. The publication was owned by Strang Communications, a Christian multimedia company based in Lake Mary, Florida.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine focused on topics such as faith, family, relationships, health, and career advice, and offered practical tips and inspiration for Christian men. New Man also featured celebrity interviews, book and music reviews, and articles about sports, fitness, and outdoor activities.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'New Man was known for its conservative Christian worldview and was considered a leading magazine of the Christian men''s movement in the late 1980s and early 1990s. Some of the notable writers who contributed to the magazine over the years include James Dobson, Chuck Colson, and Tony Campolo.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2007, the magazine ceased publication due to declining advertising revenues and a changing media landscape. However, New Man''s impact on the Christian men''s movement has been noted by scholars and commentators, and the publication remains an important record of the intersection of faith and masculinity in the United States during the latter part of the 20th century.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Figaro Magazine
