INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Flying Aces', N'flying-aces', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A pulp publication from 1928-1944, focusing on aviation fiction and adventure, known for its high-quality content and illustrations.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Flying Aces was a preeminent literary medium largely focusing on aviation, fiction, and notably, the genre of the pulp magazine. Established in the United States in 1928, it offered a vibrant exploration of flight technology, combat stories, and adventure tales until its culmination in 1944.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'This periodical was the brainchild of Periodical House, Inc., a New York-based publisher known for generating content that captivated audiences with gripping narratives and visual stimuli. The publication found a steadfast audience among adventure-seekers and aviation enthusiasts alike, promising tales of daring endeavors, historic engagements, and awe-inspiring chronicles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Flying Aces was renowned for the high standard of it''s content, covering a spectrum of subjects that included informative articles about aircraft, serialized novels, and action-adventure short stories. The magazine''s depiction of air adventure was especially immersive, enabling readers to virtually experience the pulsating thrills of aerial combats and chivalry high above the trenches.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the most distinctive facets of Flying Aces was its portfolio of illustrators and writers. Authenticity was a crux in the publication, and to maintain this, it drew upon the expertise of renowned authors such as Donald Keyhoe, Arch Whitehouse, and O.B. Myers. Through the pens of these narrative craftsmen, the magazine''s tales retained an air of veracity, transporting readers into the throbbing heart of skies aflame with dogfights and high-octane pursuits.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'An equally integral part of the magazine''s distinct identity was formed by its intricate cover designs. Fred Meagher, an esteemed illustrator and veteran of World War I, lent his master strokes, portraying aircrafts and war scenes with surgical precision and ineffable dynamism. These images became synonymous with the publication, weaving tales before the pages were even turned.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over time, Flying Aces became a migratory stage for talents transitioning from the pulp magazine industry to mainstream book publication. Luminaries such as Robert Sidney Bowen and Raoul Whitfield propelled their careers forward using the Flying Aces platform, shaping the realm of aviation literature and inspiring an entire generation of aviation story enthusiasts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Clean and compact in its delivery, Flying Aces redefined the spectrum of aviation literature. More than a magazine, it was a beacon for those drawn to the heady blend of history, technology, and human valor found in the world of aviation.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Flying Models
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Flying Models', N'flying-models', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American magazine (1928-2014) dedicated to model aviation enthusiasts, featuring construction guides, reviews, and community events.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Flying Models, an American-based publication, was cherished by aviation aficionados and model hobbyists alike for its dedicated coverage of model aviation. The magazine commenced its journey in 1928, delivering knowledge, insights, and inspiration to its readership until it ceased publication in 2014.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s publishing house, Carstens Publications, Inc, known for a diverse array of hobbyist-centric content, was instrumental in transforming Flying Models into a cornerstone within the model aviation community. Throughout its 86-year tenure, the magazine remained faithful to its pivotal role of steering readers through the fascinating world of aerodynamic design, construction techniques, and the mastering of model flight.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Flying Models was widely appreciated for its intricate focus on all niches of model aviation. Be it free-flight, control-line, radio control, or indoor flight models, the magazine proved an invaluable guide. Enriched with comprehensive articles, in-depth reviews, and connective editorials, it encouraged both beginners and veterans to explore the universe of miniature aviation in all its splendid diversity.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'An illustrious ensemble of writers and contributors lent their expertise to Flying Models. Esteemed veterans like Don Ross, Walt Mooney, and Nick Ziroli penned articles, guides, and tips, their collective knowledge resonating in each page, guiding readers through the nuances of model flight with precision and passion.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of Flying Models'' distinguishing features was the inclusion of detailed construction plans. These ranged from simple beginner models to complex competition designs. Coupled with comprehensive instructional guides and exquisite photographic accompaniments, these plans provided readers with the complete toolset to bring their aviation models to life.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Furthermore, the magazine kept its readership updated on the pulse of the model aviation community, with regular features on events, competitions, and showcases across the globe. Its pages were a platform for enthusiasts not only to learn but also to connect, share experiences, and celebrate their achievements.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its lifetime, Flying Models did not just print pages; it shaped experiences. It incubated dreams, nurtured curiosity, and fulfilled the demand for quality knowledge in the realm of model aviation, proving an integral part of the fabric of the entire hobbyist community.', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Football Digest
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Football Digest', N'football.digest', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American publication (1970-present) offering insightful coverage of the NFL through features, team analyses, and game statistics.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Football Digest, founded in 1970 and published by Century Publishing based in Evanston, Illinois, is a premier publication dedicated to the enthralling sport of American football. This compact-sized magazine quickly gained a cherished reputation for its stellar coverage of professional football, with particular attention to the National Football League (NFL).' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s content, uniquely concise and comprehensive, offered readers its signature mix of feature articles, team assessments, player bios, and game statistics. Notable writers within the domain of sports journalism contributed to this esteemed publication, drawing in readers with their vivid storytelling and insightful commentary.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Emerging as a bastion for true football purists, Football Digest presented each issue with a cover story generally profiling a renowned player or a critical turning point in the football season. Additionally, ''Scouting Reports'', an integral section of the magazine, augmented fans'' understanding of team strategies, forging intimate connections between on-field actions and spectators'' perceptions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Known for its accessibility and readability, football Digest stood apart from other sports publications. Its format of recreating the top ten games of the previous month into an engaging ''printcast'' was a fan favorite. These game recaps, written with a passion and precision akin to radio narration, offered readers the excitement of reliving these iconic matches.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'''The Thinking Man''s Guide to Pro Football'' and ''Digest Poll'', were among the other exceptionally popular features. The annual NFL player poll, in particular, drew widespread attention for offering unique insights into player perspectives concerning their peers, coaches, and the sport overall.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'More so than any other sports magazine of its time, Football Digest served as a vibrant chronicle embodying the spirit and tenacity inherent to football. It provided fans with a deeper understanding of the players, teams, and dynamics that constituted the pulse of the National Football League. In doing so, the magazine underscored its role as a torchbearer in the realm of football journalism.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- For Men Only
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'For Men Only', N'for-men-only', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Mid-20th century men''s adventure magazine laden with high-octane narratives, masculine features, and scantily-clad pin-ups.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'For Men Only, a now-defunct magazine, was an American popular men''s periodical that rose to prominence in the mid-20th century. First published in August 1950 by Canam Publishers Sales Corp., the magazine was part of the wave of men''s adventure magazines, also colloquially termed as "the sweats," in postwar America.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s content was a testosterone-fueled melange that encompassed real and fictional tales of peril and bravery, interspersed with eye-catching pin-up illustrations. This peculiar blend of rugged adventure narratives and racy imagery was aimed at sating a burgeoning readership among American men in the throes of post-war cultural metamorphosis.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Known for its sensational storytelling, For Men Only exhibited a remarkable penchant for graphic tales often set against backdrop of wars, expeditions, and explorations. These narratives strove to evoke the primal instincts in readers, often spotlighting scenarios of ''man versus wild'', ''man against man'', and the timeless ''damsel in distress''. These stories, though far from the realm of literary classics, served as prized escapism for an entire generation of men.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Distinguished illustrators of that era, including Norman Saunders, James Bama, and Mort Künstler, graced the magazine''s pages with their vivid and risqué depictions. These artworks were not merely ornamentation; they substantiated the hypermasculine narratives, becoming the visual cornerstone of For Men Only.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine carried a robust tradition of featuring articles on survival skills, sporting accounts, and profiles of inspiring adventurers, further reinforcing its masculine appeal. Yet, on the same token, it bore a distinctive pandering to male fantasies, evidenced in its liberal showcasing of scantily-clad women.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The daring audacity of For Men Only etched an indelible mark in the annals of magazine publishing. Its uninhibited portrayal of men''s fantasies and aspirations came to define a genre and era, offering a unique prism into the shifting paradigm of post-war American masculinity. Even though the ink of the last issue has long dried, its legacy forms a riveting chapter in the annals of American publishing.', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Forced Exposure
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Forced Exposure', N'forced-exposure', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American counterculture magazine renowned for eclectic music and arts coverage; also a record label and online distribution platform.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Forced Exposure is a notable counterculture periodical hailing from the United States, renowned for its unique perspective on the music and arts scene. The magazine was founded in 1980 in Boston, Massachusetts by Jimmy Johnson and Byron Coley, two figures ingrained in the alternative music community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Initially distributed as a fanzine, Forced Exposure began its journey spotlighting the burgeoning hardcore punk scene. The magazine rapidly garnered a reputation for its incisive, thorough, and at times confrontational reviews of records and live music. Their extensive coverage provided an in-depth examination of then-underground music scenes, serving as a comprehensive record of an era that transformed the American music landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In its early years, Forced Exposure had a pronounced focus on hardcore punk, indie rock, and no wave genres. However, with the passage of time, the magazine expanded its purview to include noise music, experimental rock, and other fringe genres within its review sphere. Additionally, it went beyond strictly musical content, featuring interviews with offbeat film directors, avant-garde visual artists, and underground poets. This eclectic mix of content mirrored the maverick spirit of Forced Exposure, which consistently disregarded mainstream conventions to illuminate the fringe.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine, in addition to its printed issues, also branched into a record label that released music across a range of genres. Although it ceased print publication in 1993, Forced Exposure''s influence has persisted in the digital age. It transitioned to an online platform, offering record distribution, and continues to be a thriving hub for underground and experimental music exploration.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Forced Exposure stands as a testament to the passion for the unconventional. Its significance lies not only in its championing of the underground scene but also in its refusal to conform to mainstream tastes. The magazine''s legacy is one of audacity and rigor, a beacon for innovation within the music and arts domain.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Ford Times
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Ford Times', N'ford-times', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American lifestyle publication issued by Ford Motor Company, featuring travel stories, art, poetry, and news on Ford''s automobile advancements.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ford Times was an iconic American lifestyle magazine that saw its inception in 1908 under the aegis of the Ford Motor Company. Commissioned to be published monthly, the magazine was originally initated as a medium for the company to reach out to its employees and automobile customers, providing them with up-to-date company news and happenings. However, Ford Times soon evolved beyond specific company concerns to encompass a broader view of American life, culture, and motoring.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The pages of Ford Times were marked by a captivating blend of travel stories, humor pieces, poetry, recipes, and striking illustrations, many of which were created by renowned artists of the time. The magazine also offered recommendations for road trips. Such well-rounded content and its artful presentation set Ford Times apart as more than just an industry-specific publication; it stood as an illustrated guide to the mid-20th-century American lifestyle and leisure, a visual treat that resonated with a wide audience.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ford Times'' unmatched characterization and commitment to art had a significant bearing on its appeal. Through engaging regular features and memorable cover designs, it carved a niche for itself in the publishing world. It was a medium where art met industry, and the charm of the magazine lay in just that - its ability to balance commercial pursuits and creative aesthetics. Ford Times enlisted the expertise of eminent painters and illustrators like Charley Harper, a modernist artist known for his distinctive wildlife illustrations.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also kept loyal Ford customers apprised of the company''s latest releases, improvements, and technological advancements. It served as a regular communication node between the Ford Motor Company and its customer base, maintaining a human touch that went well above and afar the roles assumed by typical company bulletins.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Whilst Ford Times ceased publication in 1993, almost 85 years since its commencement, the legacy it leaves behind is anything but ordinary. The magazine''s multi-faceted and broad-based approach to content, coupled with its artistic endeavor, makes it a noteworthy archive of American cultural history and automobile advancement.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Forest and Stream
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Forest and Stream', N'forest-and-stream', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription 19th-century American outdoor magazine emphasizing hunting, fishing, and conservation; instrumental in the inception of Audubon Society.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Forest and Stream, dating back to its establishment in 1873, evolved as a significant American publication in the realms of hunting, fishing, and outdoor activities. The magazine''s roots are intertwined with the environmental conservation movement, as it projected a spirit of appreciation for nature, wildlife, and the joy that outdoor adventures lend to the American way of life.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Helmed by Charles Hallock, an avid angler and conservationist, Forest and Stream served as a platform to galvanize wilderness lovers, impart outdoor skills, and disseminate news and anecdotes of hunting and fishing exploits. Its columns, brimming with rich descriptions and stories on outdoor pursuits, distinguished the magazine as a premium source of knowledge and entertainment for its readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although the content was largely defined by hunting and fishing along with other outdoor activities, Forest and Stream stood firmly as an advocate for wildlife protection and natural resource sustainability. Its editorial narratives often focused on environmental conservation issues, underscoring the necessity for regulated hunting and sustainable fishing practices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The scope of Forest and Stream extended beyond outdoor leisure and activism, reaching into the scientific and literary realms. With content curated from the writings of natural scientists, practitioners, and nature enthusiasts, the publication offered myriad perspectives on America''s natural heritage. Renowned naturalists like George Bird Grinnell, who served as the editor of the magazine, frequently graced its pages with their contributions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also played a seminal role in the inception of conservation organizations. A notable example is the Audubon Society, an early advocate for the preservation of birds and their habitats, which found its foundations in the pages of Forest and Stream.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'As such, Forest and Stream commanded a unique position in late 19th and early 20th century American media. Catering to a well-defined demographic with a synergy of outdoor recreation and environmental stewardship, it underscored the responsible enjoyment of nature''s bounty as an integral part of American life. Its legacy therefore, extends beyond mere publishing, and threads into the tapestry of American natural conservation history.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Fortune Small Business
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Fortune Small Business', N'fortune-small-business', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American publication focused on small business trends, management, and entrepreneur success stories; ceased print in 2009.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Fortune Small Business (FSB), a proud sibling publication to the titan of business journalism Fortune Magazine, catered explicitly to the unique needs and interests of small business owners across the United States. From the year of its inception in 1991, until it ceased its print issue in 2009, FSB served as a vital resource, illuminating the entrepreneurial landscape with timely, in-depth information and insightful analysis.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Established by the eminent Time Inc., FSB proffered its readers a wealth of knowledge on various facets of small business management, encompassing sectors as diverse as manufacturing to technology and retail. Its content was characterized by a blend of feature stories, strategic advice, and profiles of successful entrepreneurs, striking a careful balance between practicality and inspiration.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine stood distinguished for its focus on both macroeconomic trends and micro-level business strategies, thereby evenhandedly serving the interests of budding entrepreneurs and established business owners. FSB’s comprehensive industry reports were particularly valued for the clarity they provided on complex economic dynamics affecting small businesses.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Moreover, FSB perpetuated its commitment to budding innovation by publishing an annual list of top innovative companies. Known as the "FSB 100," this list coalesced around thriving businesses that demonstrated significant innovation, providing readers with exemplary models of entrepreneurial success.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The sections titled "The Mogul Next Door" and "Innovation Nation" were staples of FSB''s strong editorial lineup, each dealing with different aspects of the small business ecosystem. While "The Mogul Next Door” painted intimate portraits of successful neighborhood entrepreneurs, “Innovation Nation” showcased pioneers at the forefront of technological and service-oriented breakthroughs.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'FSB, by transforming small scale narratives into compelling conversations, successfully engaged a broad readership spanning business leaders, policymakers, and general business enthusiasts. Despite its culmination as a print publication in December 2009, it etched an indelible mark on the landscape of business publications. Now united with CNNMoney.com, the spirit of FSB continues to thrive in the digital vein, further extending its pivotal role in fanning the sparks of entrepreneurial spirit in America.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Forum
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Forum', N'the-forum', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Historic U.S. magazine (1885-1993) promoting intellectual discourse; published Mark Twain among others; known for open debate format.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Forum, a United States-based periodical of high repute, commenced its print journey in 1885 and spanned over a century, highly influential in disseminating critical intellectual discourse. Renowned for its commitment to candid, unrestricted discussion, the magazine was aptly named The Forum, implying an open space for public debate and scholastic exchange.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Co-founded by the illustrious partnership of Franklin H. Hooper and Isaac Lea, The Forum embarked on a mission to stimulate intellectual curiosity and provoke thought, while navigating the complex political, societal, and cultural landscapes. With its definite focus on long-form journalism, the magazine offered a thoughtful refuge from the clutter of short, focused news streams.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Forum embraced a broad spectrum of subject matter, encompassing politics, economics, culture, science, and the arts. The depth and breadth of its content rendered it a cherished intellectual companion among scholars, politicians, and the learned public. Its inclusive approach, inviting opinion and analysis from all corners of society, marked it as a democratic space in the world of magazines.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'A hallmark of The Forum was its willingness to publish dissenting viewpoints, resulting in vibrant dialogues within its pages. Its dedication to this principle led to the feature of prominent figures across the social and political spectrum, ensuring a balance of contrasting perspectives on critical issues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Notable in its legacy, The Forum was among the few select platforms that published famed author Mark Twain''s later works. Other distinguished contributors include eminent figures such as Woodrow Wilson, Elizabeth Cady Stanton, and Theodore Roosevelt, each leaving their indelible mark on the magazine’s intellectual fabric.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite multiple ownership changes and editorial tweaks, The Forum remained steadfast in its fundamental aim - to encourage enlightened discussion on pertinent issues. Over its long run, the publication evolved in format, transitioning from a hardcover magazine to a paperback periodical.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Finally, after 108 years, The Forum ceased publication in 1993. However, its formidable legacy as a crucible of intellectual exchange continues to illuminate the annals of American journalistic history. Its profound emphasis on open discussion, intellectual rigor, and diverse viewpoints has left an everlasting impact on the larger journalistic landscape.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Freedomways
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Freedomways', N'Freedomways-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American quarterly (1961-1985) illuminating African American struggle and civil rights; included works from Alice Walker, Langston Hughes.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Freedomways, an influential American quarterly periodical, emerged in the volatile socio-political climate of 1961 as a beacon of African-American intellectualism and activist thought. It continued its relentless stride in championing civil rights dialogue and discourse until its final issue in 1985.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Created amidst the tumultuous Civil Rights era, Freedomways sought to illuminate the struggle of African Americans against racial injustice. A project shaped by the dedicated collaboration of W.E.B. Du Bois, famed black scholar, and Esther Cooper Jackson and Shirley Graham Du Bois, its founding editors, the journal emerged as a prominent platform for deepening the awareness and understanding of racial equality issues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine, unique in its focus, united scholars, activists, and artists from the African American community and beyond, thereby amplifying minority voices and perspectives. It made an indelible mark in encouraging and fostering literature and art that represented the African American experience, thus shedding light on an oft-overlooked aspect of American society.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'While invariably intertwined with the cause of racial equality, Freedomways broadened its scope beyond the American borders, underscoring the interconnection of the African American struggle with Pan-Africanism, the international labor movement, and the global anti-colonial struggle. This comprehensive approach allowed it to narrate the shared experiences of oppression and resistance across countries and cultures.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Famed literary personalities like Alice Walker and Langston Hughes found a congenial platform in Freedomways to express their creative prowess, their works unveiling the African American context and contributing to a more nuanced understanding of collective racial justice. The magazine also featured an impressive line-up of political figures who conveyed their vision for racial equality within its pages.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Freedomways'' remarkable commitment to voicing the perspectives of racial minorities, stimulating intellectual discourse, and advocating social justice maintained its relevance across the globe. It persistently stood as a testament to the inextricable link between knowledge, creativity, and the enduring struggle for racial equality. The magazine may have ceased publication, but its impact is an inalienable aspect of journalistic and intellectual history.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Freshmen Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Freshmen Magazine', N'freshmen-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American monthly magazine (1982-2009) focused on gay lifestyle and erotica, also addressing socio-political issues in the LGBTQ+ community.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Freshmen, an American monthly magazine, first dawned in the publishing scene in 1982, forging a distinct image in print media that catered specifically to a gay audience. Published by Specialty Publications, a branch of LPI Media, this periodical upheld a unique and compelling niche, contributing significantly to gay cultural dialogue and representation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With an overarching aim to celebrate and highlight the diversity of gay culture and lifestyle, Freshmen offered its readers an immersive exploration of gay narratives, experiences, and perspectives. The magazine''s striking portrayal of youthful vibrancy echoed throughout its pages, creating a resonant platform for myriad voices within the gay community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the distinct features of Freshmen was its commitment to unmasking authentic gay experiences and narratives. Its in-depth interviews and candid profiles of various personalities provided the readers a rare collective insight into the individual and shared experiences of the gay community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Not merely relegated to the portrayal of gay life, Freshmen also played a monumental role in the annals of gay erotica, boasting a substantial readership drawn by its photographic spreads. It elegantly juggled its role as a charted sector for gay erotica whilst simultaneously promoting a broader sense of community, understanding, and acceptance of gay culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Moreover, the magazine did not shy away from delving into serious discussions pertaining to AIDS, gay rights, societal acceptance, and ongoing legislative battles pertinent to the LGBTQ+ community. By doing so, Freshmen cemented its reputation as not merely an adult publication but a significant catalyst for discourse on important socio-political issues affecting its target readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its years of publication, Freshmen remained a steadfast beacon in gay literature, carving out a unique landscape where numerous identities, narratives, and viewpoints melded together, epitomizing the vibrant and diverse spectrum of gay culture. Its role in setting a narrative stage that firmly encapsulated the true color of the gay community has etched it incontestably into the fabric of LGBTQ+ cultural history.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Friendship and Freedom
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Friendship and Freedom', N'friendship-and-freedom', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription 1921 American magazine by YWCA fostering interracial dialogue and understanding, promoting racial harmony in the era of segregation.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Friendship and Freedom, a groundbreaking publication of significant import, embarked upon capturing the attention of the American reading audience in 1921. Published by the Young Women''s Christian Association (YWCA), it traversed a pioneering path, serving as a beacon of allyship for Black and white women in the pursuit of racial equality.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Instigating crucial dialogue between different racial groups, Friendship and Freedom emerged as a compelling voice in the push for racial harmony during the pivotal era of the 1920s. It unfolded an unpreceded bridge of communication, aiming to disintegrate the prevalent racial barriers that marred the American landscape of the time.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Every issue of Friendship and Freedom bore testimony to resolute efforts in fostering interracial understanding. This was remarkably evident through its variety of articles, personal narratives, poetry, and news briefs. The content represented a diverse array of voices, standing as a testament to the shared aspiration of racial unity.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Another crucial stride that Friendship and Freedom undertook was its explicit attention towards the acknowledgement and understanding of the ''Negro problem.'' Through a series of enlightening features and discussions, the magazine strove to sensitize its primarily white readership about the deplorable racial struggles faced by their Black counterparts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The editors of Friendship and Freedom employed a unique editorial tactic. Rather than claim a firm stance on particular issues, they utilized a more subtle approach, channeling their agenda through illuminating narratives, thought-provoking commentaries, and discrete, symbolic illustrations. The objective was to inspire self-reflection and foster individual interpretation among the readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also unabashedly provided a steady platform for the display of Black excellence. It routinely honored Black contributors and highlighted their accomplishments in various arenas - education, arts and literature, women''s rights, and civil rights advocacy. Such representation worked towards dismantling racial stereotypes and cultivating respect and appreciation for Black culture and intellect.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although Friendship and Freedom was only in circulation for under a year, its influence permeates the annals of American periodical history for its audacious pursuit of racial harmony. Indeed, its legacy remains, serving as a tantalizing mirror to an era of crucial racial discourse and marking an early endeavor towards forging a path of racial understanding and unity in America.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- FringeWare Review
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'FringeWare Review', N'fringeWare-review', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription 1992-1998 magazine exploring the confluence of counterculture and cyberculture, with focus on fringe, marginalized ideas and phenomena.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'FringeWare Review, a provocative and pioneering publication, commenced its delectable journey into the creative stratosphere in 1992. This unique piece of print was conceived and nurtured by Paco Nathan and Mondo 2000 alum Gareth Branwyn. As a platform, FringeWare Review strived to meld counterculture and computer subculture into a tantalizing fusion, providing thought-provoking content to the intrigued audience.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Breaking the conventional dimensions of magazine themes, FringeWare Review reveled in the unconventional. It focused on cyberculture, while exploring fringe, marginalized ideas and phenomena, thereby enriching the cultural lexicon. The magazine''s content ranged from articles on cyberpunk to visual culture, transgressive sexuality to techno-anarchy. Each edition convincingly established the publication as a galvanizing forum of intellectual discourse.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Promoting an amalgamation of high-tech and art, FringeWare Review sought to expose the readership to eccentricities and the unexplored facets of culture, integrating marginal and mainstream narratives in each issue. The magazine offered an eclectic mix of persona and topics, unabashedly confronting taboo subjects and veiled constructs of society with equal vigor and charm.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Complementing the magazine''s cutting-edge textual content was its striking visual components. Its pages invited the eyes with a surreal blend of imagery, oscillating between the bizarre, the outlandish, and the profoundly ingenious. The aesthetic sensibilities of FringeWare Review augmented its intellectual appeal, successfully immersing its audience within its captivating world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'FringeWare Review also served as the namesake of a concurrently-operating online store, FringeWare, that dealt in offbeat products, eccentric literature, and unconventional software. The synergistic existence of the magazine with the online store made FringeWare a one-of-its-kind endeavor, shaking up the realms of printed and digital distribution.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s pages contained refreshing, idiosyncratically delivered perspectives, combining academic rigor with underground cultural meditations. All of these were intricately woven within the bimonthly issues, making FringeWare Review an illuminated tapestry of cyberculture and counterculture exploration.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Within its brief existence from 1992 to 1998, FringeWare Review carved out a singular niche for itself within the printed media landscape. By spotlighting the fringe, it informed, quested, and pushed boundaries, crafting an unforgettable legacy within the annals of alternative print culture.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Frontiers Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Frontiers Magazine', N'frontiers-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Biweekly LGBTQ+ publication active from 1981-2016, focusing on rights advocacy, cultural commentary, and community connectivity.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Frontiers, a trailblazer in the field of LGBTQ+ journalism, originated amid the vibrant societal turbulence of 1981 Los Angeles. Conceived by the enterprising minds of Bob Craig and David Stern, this biweekly publication endeavored to provide a voice for the often marginalized LGBTQ+ community and swiftly became synonymous with the struggle for rights and acceptance, providing a beacon for the progressive cause.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Frontiers represented a powerful and candid platform that underscored the socio-political realities, triumphs, and tribulations of the LGBTQ+ community. The magazine served as a critical link between the constantly evolving public sentiment and the ground-level realities within the community, lending invaluable insights into a wide array of topics concerning human rights, sexuality, health, politics, and culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Broad in its scope, yet laser-focused in its approach, Frontiers navigated myriad subjects. Detailing the community''s battles with HIV/AIDS, advocating for same-sex marriage rights, highlighting the fight for broader societal acceptance, and giving exposure to emerging LGBTQ+ artists and their works, the magazine was unyielding in its mission, earning its place as a pivotal player in local and national dialogues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to probing narratives and articles, Frontiers bolstered its content with exquisite visual dimensions. Unafraid to illuminate the full spectrum of LGBTQ+ lifestyles, portraits of real individuals paired with spotlight features on notable personalities were chronicled amidst a cascade of colorful photography, contributing to the magazine''s overarching narrative of diversity and authenticity.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Distinct from other LGBTQ+ publications of its time, Frontiers nurtured a symbiotic relationship with its audience, harnessing reader-generated content to drive dialogues. The magazine''s acclaimed ''Letters to the Editor'' section served as a cherished conduit for readers to voice their opinions, share personal narratives, and dialogue with fellow members of the community. This interplay fostered a sense of belonging, fortifying Frontiers'' identity as a communal platform.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Beyond its editorial accomplishments, Frontiers was commendable in its commitment to the business side of publishing. It aggressively pursued advertising relationships with prominent LGBTQ+ friendly businesses, thereby sustaining its financial stability in an era when LGBTQ+ publications often struggled to remain viable.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'From its inception in 1981 until ceasing publication in 2016, Frontiers was much more than a magazine - it was an instrument of discourse, a microphone for the voiceless, and a testament to the resilience and evolution of the LGBTQ+ community throughout changing times. Its indelible legacy remains etched into the annals of advocacy journalism.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Fuji Flyer
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Fuji Flyer', N'fuji-flyer', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A prestigious Japanese aviation publication providing in-depth industry insights since 1982.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Fuji Flyer" (富士フライヤー) is a prestigious Japanese publication that has garnered recognition and respect in its numerous years of operation. It has been an instrumental source of airborne and aviation content, establishing itself as a significant influence in global aviation discourse.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'First published in 1982, "Fuji Flyer," whose native name, 富士フライヤー, constitutes a homonym to Japan''s iconic Mt. Fuji, has been an indomitable purveyor of aviation knowledge. The magazine is renowned for its comprehensive focus on a broad spectrum of topics within the realm of air transport, aviation technology, and affiliated industries.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'For the non-Japanese world, Fuji Flyer Magazine acquires an attribute of authenticity, providing a cultural perspective on the aviation industry, with a decidedly Japanese tinge. Each monthly issue incorporates meticulously researched articles, industry news, expert interviews, and aircraft reviews. The Fuji Flyer showcases the East Asian stance on flying and aircraft, helping to diversify the typically western-centric aviation narrative.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Headquartered in Tokyo, "Fuji Flyer" renders encyclopedic knowledge as it fuses technical complexities with mainstream readability. Its English-translated variant, while faithfully retaining its cognitive depth, has proven immensely appealing to a global readership. As a testament to its international reach and reputation, "Fuji Flyer" is widely accessible in airports and major bookstores across continents.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Moreover, the magazine hosts an array of distinguished writing talents ranging from aircraft engineers to experienced pilots, and flight enthusiasts. This pool of diverse contributors further escalates its credibility, rendering it a veritable platform for the exchange of ground-breaking ideas and the latest breakthroughs in aviation technology.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With its quintessential Japanese precision, the editorial team of "Fuji Flyer" diligently adheres to stringent fact-checking procedures, ensuring that every piece of content is accurate, informative, and up-to-date. The magazine''s vast and ardent readership relies on this unwavering commitment, resulting in an influential voice in the expansive and perpetually evolving realm of aviation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The legacy of the "Fuji Flyer" stands as a beacon amongst aviation literature. Its unique lexicon of air travel, technology, and industry trends provides immediate relevance for its devout readership and new enthusiasts alike, forging a rich and respected narrative within global aviation discourse.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Fur Worker
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Fur Worker', N'the-fur-worker', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription German-originated American periodical for fur industry professionals, featuring industry news, artisan advice, and market trends.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"The Fur Worker," (Der Pelzarbeiter) an eminent American periodical primarily published in German, has held a distinguished position in the fur industry''s literature since its inception. Having underpinned various transitions within the trade, from artisanship to mechanization, the publication''s documentation provides valued discernment into the socio-economic undercurrents of North America''s fur industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Making its debut in the year 1885 with the aim of promoting and educating fur workers in the United States and beyond, "The Fur Worker," initially published solely in German as "Der Pelzarbeiter," became a juggernaut for the exchange of practices, trends, and legislation related to the fur industry. Its cross-continental pioneering role innately makes it a linchpin offering deep insights about the interplay of fashion, economy, and society.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is headquartered in New York, once considered the epicenter of fur trade during the 20th century. This strategically located base has allowed "The Fur Worker" a firsthand perspective on the significant developments within the industry, enabling it to capture the dynamics of the market with operose detail.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"The Fur Worker" stands out for its comprehensive engagement with the fur industry''s multifaceted composition. Each edition not only consists of industry news and regulatory updates, but it also offers practical advice columns for artisans. Furthermore, the forum sheds light on advancements in technology and new techniques in fur processing, thereby maintaining its relevancy amidst the fur industry''s metamorphosis.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine has succeeded in binding a diverse array of writers under its name, from accomplished fur designers to industry analysts. This diverse catalog of contributors enriches the publication''s reputation, providing thought-leadership and factual representation of the industry''s landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the notable characteristics of "The Fur Worker" is its meticulous adherence to the principles of journalistic integrity. The magazine consistently ensures the accuracy and erudition of each article, with a strict lean towards presenting an unbiased portrayal of the industry at large. This steadfast commitment to factual representation enhances the publication''s credibility, situating it as a respected bastion in the fur trade discourse.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Delighting in the challenge of demystifying a globally significant yet understudied industry, the legacy of "The Fur Worker" exists as a vital continuum within fur trade literature. Its potent blend of trade development updates, artisan insights, and market predictions proffer an unrivaled understanding of the fur industry''s historical contour and its future trajectories.', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Furniture Style
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Furniture Style', N'furniture-style', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American periodical for interior design industry, covering furniture trends, market updates, and purchasing advice.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Furniture Style," is a highly regarded American periodical that constitutes a remarkable presence within the realm of interior design, specifically tailored to the furniture industry. Documenting various design movements and innovations, it has become a pivotal publication for professionals, enthusiasts, and industry insiders.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Established in 1997, "Furniture Style" addresses a multitude of interests, built upon the orchestrations of prominent decorators, artists, and manufacturers. It serves as a platform for the discussions of furniture trends, industry updates, and sound advice on purchasing decisions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The headquarters of "Furniture Style," nestled in the fast-paced city of Chicago, presents a strategic vantage point that encapsulates the dynamic advances within the furniture industry. This positioning enables the magazine to provide its readership with an encompassing view of national and international trends.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Furniture Style" effectively communicates the many layers of the furniture industry. Every issue features industry news and commentary, reviews of furniture collections, showcases of upcoming designers, and practical advice for furniture retailing. It serves as a practical and inspiring repository for the furniture marketplace.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'A key strength of "Furniture Style" lies in its diverse authorship. Its array of contributors ranges from renowned interior designers to astute industry analysts offering a comprehensive, multi-faceted perspective to its readers. This diversity ensures a rich content mix, unique perspectives, and a comprehensive overview of the industry''s landscape.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Consistently displaying high standards of journalistic integrity, "Furniture Style" adheres closely to the accuracy of facts and impartiality of viewpoint. It maintains this commitment, providing its readership with trustworthy and informative content about the industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In all, "Furniture Style" sits at the forefront of the furniture industry''s publications, embodying a renowned touchstone for designers, manufacturers, and enthusiasts alike. Commanding a compelling mix of design trends, market analysis, and retail advice, this etalon remains a force to be reckoned with amidst furniture trade literature, serving as a singularly insightful guide to the larger discourse of the industry.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Fusion Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Fusion Magazine', N'fusion-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American music periodical highlighting wide-ranging genres, featuring interviews, album reviews, and industry insights.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Fusion" is an esteemed American music magazine, prominently situated in the intersection of musical genres. Since its inception in 1967, it has been offering an enlightening perspective on the world of music, primarily within the realm of rock, but with a distinctive appreciation for the eclectic blend of genres.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Anchored in Boston, Massachusetts, "Fusion" presents itself as a medium of interaction between the creators and audience. The magazine is highly regarded for its insightful commentary, the exploration of various music styles, and the promotion of emerging talents.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With its staunch dedication to the binding versatility of music, "Fusion" diligently covers a blend of genres, from Rock to Jazz, Blues to Classical, Folk to Experimental, making it a dynamic and diverse platform for music discussion. Each issue brings a repertoire of features, including comprehensive interviews, album reviews, and stories that delve into the world of artists across the spectrum.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The journalistic integrity that "Fusion" upholds is one of its hallmarks. Its rich palette of contributors includes renowned music critics, industry insiders, and passionate aficionados. Their collective wisdom forms the backbone of the magazine, empowering insightful narratives and informed critiques.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Fusion" consistently chronicles the evolution of music, identifying trends, highlighting achievements, and engaging with issues relevant to the industry. Among its memorable pages, one may expect the discovery of a fresh indie band, the celebration of an album anniversary of an established artist, or a dissection of an avant-garde music performance.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Embedded within its creative ethos is a commitment to both mainstream and counterculture, documenting celebrated classics and groundbreaking innovations side by side. The result is a fine balance that reflects the shifting paradigms of the music world while paying homage to its roots.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Fusion," with its incisive commentary and eclectic coverage, has cemented its place as a vital resource for avid music lovers and industry professionals, expanding horizons, and shaping conversations in the musical landscape. It remains a beacon of the contemporary music scene, shining a light on the past, present, and future of music in its manifold forms.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Future Sex
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Future Sex', N'future-Sex-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Publication exploring intersection of technology and sexuality, fostering dialogue on intimacy and relationships in the digital age.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Future Sex", an avant-garde digital and print publication, entered the media sphere in 2014, presenting a unique exploration into sexuality and technology. The magazine''s core ethos revolves around the understanding and portrayal of how these two integral facets of human existence harmonize in the modern world. Originally published in Berlin, Germany, "Future Sex" offers a bold, contemporary perspective on intimate issues, presented through a variety of multimedia formats.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Future Sex" challenges traditional norms and fosters a dialogue about the intersection of technology, intimacy, and personal relationships. Striving for inclusivity, the magazine covers a broad spectrum of topics related to sexuality, making its content appealing to a broad, diverse readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine distinguishes itself with its innovative design and thought-provoking content, including interviews, op-eds, and features focused on the ever-evolving landscape of human intimacy in the modern world. From investigations into virtual reality and sex, to features on sex robots and adult applications, "Future Sex" asks its readership to contemplate what may lie on the horizon.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Falling under the umbrella of ethical journalism, "Future Sex" takes great care to approach sensitive topics with due respect, aiming to inform and enlighten without crossing boundaries of propriety. Its content includes contributions from some of the industry''s top writers, academicians, and experts in the field of technology and intimacy.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is lauded for not shying away from challenging discussions and embracing a philosophy that encourages open dialogue about the future of sex. Despite its relative newness, its provocative, yet insightful content has successfully pushed "Future Sex" into the limelight, transforming it into an influential voice within the industry.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gadfly Online
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Gadfly Online', N'gadfly-online', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Web-based and annual print publication exploring culture, politics, and society through intellectual, provocative content.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gadfly Online, a provocative and influential publication, entered the media landscape in 1997, swiftly establishing itself as an integral platform for intellectual discourse. Functioning as a catalyst for engaging and thought-provoking dialogues, Gadfly Online has become renowned for its fearless exploration of culture, politics, and society.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Founded by Jeremy Landau and Jared Brown, the magazine operates out of Lawrence, Kansas and boasts a fervent readership that extends well beyond its geographical origins. While primarily known for its web presence, Gadfly Online also manifests in annual print formats, curating a compilation of the most highly-acclaimed articles of the year.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine is distinguished by its dedication to interweaving nuanced and intellectual analysis with topical relevance. Its uncompromising and evocative content, posed through features, interviews, and opinion pieces, paints the socio-political landscape with stark recognition and fierce boldness. Art, politics, culture, and their intertwined dynamics serve as the primary foci of Gadfly Online''s inquiries.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The success of Gadfly Online lies not merely in its edifying content, but also in its efforts to bring lesser-known artists, musicians, writers, and political figures to the foreground. By embracing voices that veer away from the mainstream, Gadfly Online proactively contributes to an egalitarian media ecosystem.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With a team of seasoned editors and ardent contributors, Gadfly Online successfully explores the cultural fabric of contemporary society. It stimulates conversations that push boundaries, challenge norms, and, ultimately, inform its readers on a wide spectrum of topics, fostering a conscientious and engaged readership.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Gaited Horse
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Gaited Horse', N'the-gaited-horse', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription North American publication dedicated to non-trotting horse breeds, focusing on care, training, health, and equestrian events.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"The Gaited Horse", a specialized North American publication, came into existence with the core aim of catering to the informational needs of aficionados and enthusiasts of naturally gaited horses. Since its inception, it has become a beacon of knowledge and insight, focusing particularly on non-trotting horse breeds.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s mandate encompasses myriad facets of gaited horse care, training, health, and riding techniques. It opens up pathways for discourse about the intricacies, beauty, and distinctions of these equine types, encouraging a better understanding of such unique breeds. The Gaited Horse Magazine illustrates and examines the variances across different breeds, such as Icelandic horses, Paso Finos, Tennessee Walking Horses, and many more.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With a hands-on, practical approach, "The Gaited Horse" contains articles by accomplished veterinarians, renowned trainers, and industry professionals. This commitment to quality content ensures that readers receive actionable and helpful advice, enabling them to improve their personal practice of horsemanship.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also upholds notable coverage of various gaited horse shows, exhibitions, and competitions across North America, chronicling key performances along with expert analysis of the presented gaits. This replication of the vibrant equestrian scene not only informs readers, but it also solidifies the magazine''s celebration of the gaited horse community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'True to its niche specialization, "The Gaited Horse" has become a trusted resource, a conduit for invaluable knowledge about gaited horse breeds. It continues to elevate generations of horse lovers'' understanding while showcasing the sheer variety and unique qualities inherent in these versatile equine breeds.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Galaxy
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Galaxy', N'the-galaxy-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription 19th-century U.S. periodical featuring serialized novels, short stories, essays, and scientific, historical, social discourse.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"The Galaxy", a highly regarded and influential periodical, was a cornerstone of American literary and sociopolitical culture during the latter half of the 19th century. Making its debut in 1866, the magazine was a potent platform for serialized novels, captivating short stories, astute essays, and critical editorial narratives. Throughout its existence, it stood as a testament to the richness and versatility of American intellectual thought and creative prowess.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Carving out a niche amidst other contemporary publications, "The Galaxy" was established under the co-editorship of William Conant Church, the seasoned journalist, and his brother Francis P. Church, the equally accomplished editor. Their editorial finesse turned it into a beacon for progressive and informed discourse.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Notable authors such as Mark Twain, Anthony Trollope, and Rebecca Harding Davis graced its covers, lending credence to the publication''s reputation as a destination for established literary figures. Twain''s "Memories of California and the Pacific" and Harding Davis'' collected essays are memorable instances of the magazine''s offerings.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its literary prowess, "The Galaxy" showcased essays dealing with scientific, historical, and social topics generating intellectual curiosity among its readers. Its "Scientific Miscellany" section was an open nod to enlightenment ideals, advocating for scientific temperance amidst existing readers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Altogether, "The Galaxy" played a significant role in shaping the American literary and intellectual landscape. The magazine''s legacy carries potent remnants of the cultural transformation and intellectual evolution that it contributed to and continues to inspire literary scholars in understanding the dynamism of the 19th century''s cultural milieu.', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Game Developer
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Game Developer', N'game-developer-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Industry-oriented publication (1994-2013) providing comprehensive analysis and insider perspectives on video game development.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Game Developer" magazine emerged in the late 20th century as a premier publication focused on the burgeoning video game industry. Established in 1994 by Miller Freeman, inc., under the editorial direction of industry veterans, the magazine quickly became an indispensable resource for both established professionals and aspiring newcomers in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Renowned for its in-depth analysis, "Game Developer" chronicled the evolution of video game design and development, including technical nuances, artistic techniques, and the complexity of the business landscape within the gaming industry. It was instrumental in bridging the chasm between game design theory and practical development, offering invaluable insights and bridging the gap between conceptualizing and creating innovative games.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Each issue of the "Game Developer" delved deep into the many facets of the industry, from interviews with leading game developers to detailed postmortems of popular games. The magazine also regularly featured articles on the latest technological advancements, programming techniques, game design methodologies, and industry trends. Notably, the magazine recognized and celebrated the achievements and innovations within the gaming sector through its annual Game Developers Choice Awards.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Game Developer’s" dedication to high-quality content, created by industry insiders, helped shape the conversations surrounding video game design. Readers benefited greatly from lessons learned by top professionals in the field, enriching their understanding of the industry and contributing to the magazine’s status as a revered resource.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Albeit no longer in print as of 2013, the magazine''s legacy lives on in its digital twin - the Gamasutra website. The influence of "Game Developer" remains a testament to its success in capturing and fostering the dynamic, creative spirit of the video game industry.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Game Players
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Game Players', N'game-players-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Defunct American gaming magazine (1989-1998) known for comprehensive console game coverage and irreverent tone.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Game Players" is a defunct American bimonthly video game magazine that carved a unique place in gaming literature during the digital entertainment explosion of the late 20th century. Founded in 1989 by Robert Lock, under Signal Research, the magazine was dedicated to providing comprehensive coverage on console gaming culture, including news, previews, reviews, and other related content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The initial focus of "Game Players" was squarely on the then-popular Nintendo platforms, including the Nintendo Entertainment System and the Game Boy, but with the launch of Sega''s Genesis system, the magazine expanded its coverage. In 1991, the publication was renamed "Game Players Sega and Nintendo Guide", a reflection of its inclusive editorial coverage. By the mid-1990s, as Sony and other manufacturers entered the market, "Game Players" broadened its scope to cover all major gaming systems.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Known for its irreverent editorial tone and in-depth reviews, "Game Players" garnered a wide readership with its attention to qualitative content. Iconic sections in the magazine included features on strategies and cheats, as well as Game Doctor, a column addressing the readers'' gaming issues with an informal, cheeky dialogue. Simultaneously, it maintained a strong focus on in-depth reviews and previews, ensuring that readers were well-informed about the latest releases.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout the 1990s, "Game Players" went through several name changes and evolutions, reflecting not only changing market dynamics but also different editorial management and ownerships. In 1996, it was morphed into Ultra Game Players. Ultimately, in 1998, it transformed into Game Buyer, before all publication was ceased by Imagine Media.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its years of publication, "Game Players" played a central role in shaping the landscape of video game journalism. Its extensive coverage and distinct voice marked it as a vital chronicle of an industry in rapid evolution, capturing the rich tapestry of the video game culture of its time.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Games Unplugged
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Games Unplugged', N'games-unplugged', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American magazine (2000-2002) dedicated to board games, card games, tabletop role-playing, and miniature war games.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"Games Unplugged" was an American monthly magazine, primarily focused on the coverage of analogue or non-electronic games. Established in 2000, under the initial publisher, Fast Forward Entertainment, the magazine held a distinctive niche within the gaming literature, centering on traditional gaming forms amidst a global shift towards digital recreation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The publication''s thematic focus encompassed the broad realm of non-digital gaming, including board games, card games, tabletop role-playing games, and miniature war gaming. Not only did it introduce new games to its readers, but the magazine also offered intriguing gameplay strategies, insightful industry news, engaging interviews with game creators and designers, as well as comprehensive reviews.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The salient feature of "Games Unplugged" was its emphasis on the communal aspect of traditional gaming forms, underscoring the social interactions and competitive camaraderie they offered in contrast to their digital counterparts. The magazine effectively communicated the charm of such gameplay, thus garnering the appreciation of enthusiasts who admired the elaborate mechanics and tangible nature of these style of games.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In terms of content structure, "Games Unplugged" incorporated a blend of regular columns, focused features, and special theme issues. Key columns included previews of upcoming games and reviews of current ones, while features typically comprised in-depth interviews with industry luminaries or game profiles. Thematic issues were either centered around a specific game genre or timed with significant industry events, thereby curating tailored and relevant content for its readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite receiving acclaim from the traditional gaming community for its content diversity and quality, "Games Unplugged", however, was short-lived. Its final issue was published in 2002. Despite its brief tenure, the magazine left an enduring legacy, as it showcased the ongoing vitality and creative innovation within the realm of non-electronic gaming during an era of digital predominance.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The GAO Journal
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The GAO Journal', N'the-gao-journal', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription U.S. Government Accountability Office''s publication from 1981 to 1993, focusing on policy, financial management and performance metrics.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The "GAO Journal" was a significant publication by the United States Government Accountability Office, providing a crucial platform for conveying the agency''s research findings and operational insights to the public. Initiated in 1981, it served as an instrumental resource to inform government, academia, and individuals about the practical aspects of policy implementation, financial management, and performance measurement at the federal level.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The unique selling proposition of the "GAO Journal" lay in its authoritative and unbiased content. The publication was lauded for its effectiveness in unpacking complex matters related to government accountability and operations, thereby making such information accessible to a broader audience. It efficiently straddled the line between being academic yet prying, thereby asserting its distinguishing position among other government strategy journals.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Its thematic spectrum covered a wide range of topics central to government performance and accountability, sourced from GAO''s extensive audit, evaluations, and investigative endeavours. The topics encompassed diverse domains such as healthcare, defense, education, fiscal management, and regulation, along with cross-cutting government reform issues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Structurally, the "GAO Journal" combined both broad-based analysis pieces and in-depth explorations of specific subjects. These included interviews with key stakeholders, perspectives from GAO''s senior leaders, feature stories around critical issues, and analytical insights derived from GAO''s audit and investigative work. Furthermore, it often cast a spotlight on the GAO''s methodological approaches to tackling complicated issues of governmental performance measurement and evaluation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'This publication was pivotal in furnishing a deeper understanding of the intricacies and challenges associated with government operations at the Federal level. Although the "GAO Journal" discontinued its publication in 1993, its rich archive continues to serve as a treasure trove of research on key American public administration themes and issues.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The GAO Review
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The GAO Review', N'the-gao-review', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Quarterly publication by U.S. Government Accountability Office from 1966-2001, covering policy, federal management, and GAO operations.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The "GAO Review" was an esteemed quarterly publication issued by the United States Government Accountability Office, positioned at the core of the agency''s initiative to foster transparency and accountability in government operations. Commenced in 1966, this magazine served as a critical avenue for disseminating GAO''s comprehensive research, audit findings, and overarching mission to an audience encompassing government officials, researchers, and the public at large.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Distinguished for its credible and impartial content, the "GAO Review" bridged the gap between the intricate world of federal government operations and the public by deconstructing multifaceted concepts into digestible insights. Its content traversed an extensive range of topics in public policy, federal fiscal management, and the intricate operations of different sectors under government purview.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The "GAO Review" typically encompassed original research articles, interviews with high-ranking GAO officials, analytical pieces reflecting upon the agency''s inner workings, methodologies, and investigative ventures, among other content. It provided a podium to the federal government and accountability experts to communicate their perspectives, promoting a healthy exchange of ideas and learnings to further the cause of effective governance.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Covering areas as diverse as defense spending, environmental regulation, healthcare policy, and education programs, the "GAO Review" served as a repository of cutting-edge knowledge and practical insight, contributing significantly to the discourse around responsible governance and public policy.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The "GAO Review" ceased publication in 2001, but its legacy endures through its substantial catalogue of issues that continue to hold value as historical records and foundations for further research in public administration and government accountability.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Gavin Report
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Gavin Report', N'the-gavin-report', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Weekly music industry magazine from 1958-2002, detailing radio charts, music trends and hosting influential industry seminars.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'"The Gavin Report," or the "Gavin," as it was widely known, was an influential weekly music industry trade magazine, published in San Francisco, United States, from 1958 until 2002. Named after its founder, Bill Gavin, a former disc jockey and record promoter, the magazine played a pivotal role in the evolution of the American music industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Bestowed with a palpable authority in the record industry, "The Gavin Report" served myriad roles throughout its publication tenure – a segmenter of radio markets, a predictor of hit records, and a reputable mediator between radio stations and record labels. Its research-intensive content included radio chart information and playlists, in-depth interviews with notable music industry figures, and cogent commentary on industry trends and issues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Operating across the landscape of contemporary music, the magazine divided its music chart into distinctive formats, including Top 40, Adult Contemporary, Urban, Country, and more, providing a comprehensive coverage of music trends in the United States. Subsequently, these charts became benchmarks for both music programmers and record companies, chiefly due to the meticulousness of their compilation process.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Among the trailblazing initiatives undertaken by "The Gavin Report" was the "Gavin Seminar," an annual conference inaugurated in 1964 that brought industry professionals into dialogue with artists, music directors, program directors, and other influencers. These annual gatherings were particularly renowned for the "Gavin Awards," which recognized outstanding contributions to the music industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Bill Gavin’s editorial methodology, predicated on a strong belief in the symbiosis between radio and the record industry, established the ethos of "The Gavin Report". This approach garnered the enduring respect of the industry, bolstering the magazine''s reputation as one of the industry’s leading sources for music and radio insights.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The cessation of "The Gavin Report" in February 2002 underscored the end of an era in the American music industry - an industry that had been significantly shaped by Bill Gavin''s insights, initiatives, and indelible influence.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gay Chicago
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Gay Chicago', N'gay-chicago', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A premier LGBT-focused publication, covering news, events, profiles, and the evolving culture within the community.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gay Chicago Magazine' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gay Chicago Magazine was a staple publication in Chicago''s LGBT community, delivering news, events, and personal profiles that catered to the interests and needs of LGBT individuals in the region. This magazine was an invaluable tool that brought the community together, playing a significant role in shaping, informing, and enriching the city''s LGBT culture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Origin' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was initially launched as ''Gay Life'' by Ralph and Craig Gernhardt in 1975, who saw the need for an information platform for the LGBT community in Chicago. This duo understood the importance of media representation in the fight for LGBT rights and the magazine quickly became a popular and trusted source of news and events within the community.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Progression and Growth' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gay Chicago Magazine rose in prominence throughout the 1980s and 1990s collaborating with various other Chicago LGBT organizations and service providers to provide a comprehensive overview of events, businesses, and news relevant to the LGBT community. It provided readers with everything from personal anecdotes and interviews to health-related pieces and special features. In 1984, the publication was officially renamed "Gay Chicago Magazine".' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Management and Distribution' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Management of Gay Chicago Magazine was taken over by Tracy Baim in 2009, who was the co-founder of another LGBT newspaper, Windy City Times. The magazine continued its intrinsic role in the Chicago''s LGBT scene, adapting to digitalization before finally ceasing its print edition and shifting completely to the online platform in 2011.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'With nearly four decades of experience, Gay Chicago Magazine remains a significant voice within the LGBT community in Chicago. It has played a critical role in the community’s history, covering a range of topics including the rise of HIV/AIDS, equal rights movements, and the evolution of the LGBT scene in Chicago. Despite its transition to complete digitalization in 2011, Gay Chicago Magazine continues its legacy of bringing forth important and relevant content for the LGBT+ community.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gear Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Gear Magazine', N'gear-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription Ground-breaking men''s lifestyle publication renowned for bold aesthetics and thought-provoking content (1998-2003).}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'# Gear Magazine' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gear Magazine was a men''s lifestyle publication that gained brief but impactful significance in the late 1990s and early 2000s. It was well-regarded for its coverage of contemporary and thought-provoking topics, combined with a cutting-edge artistic aesthetic.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Establishment and Early Years' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Established in 1998 by Bob Guccione Jr., son of Penthouse founder Bob Guccione Sr., Gear aimed to cater to an audience interested in a wide array of modern lifestyle topics. These topics ranged from current trends in fashion and music to in-depth features on technology and contemporary issues. The U.S.-based magazine quickly gained a reputation for its daring style and brash tone, positioning itself as a distinctive voice in the male-oriented magazine market.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content and Style' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Gear Magazine was renowned for its thought-provoking features and exclusive interviews, often featuring prominent figures in pop culture, sports, and entertainment industry. These profiles marked a significant attraction for the magazine’s readership and helped in shaping its public image. The magazine also notably tapped into the emerging world of digital and information technology, providing readers with up-to-date overviews and analyses.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Moreover, Gear presented a bold and assertive aesthetic, characterized by its provocative cover designs and exceptional photography. The magazine, however, was sometimes criticized for the objectification of women in its photo spreads, stirring controversy and debates on several occasions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Closure and Legacy ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The publication came to an end in 2003, due to declining sales and mounting criticism over its content. However, during its five-year lifespan, Gear offered a unique blend of lifestyle and cultural content, establishing a distinctive identity among male-oriented magazines.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'While Gear Magazine''s operation was short-lived, its influence continues to live on as a marker of late 20th-century male-targeted publications, which encapsulated an era of rapidly evolving societal standards and cultural norms. Its provocative approach to editorial and visual content serves as a reflection of both the times it operated in and the transitional state of media during this period.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Geek Monthly
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Geek Monthly', N'geek-monthly', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American print magazine (2006-2010) dedicated to geek culture, including tech, video games, comic books, and popular science.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'# Geek Monthly' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Geek Monthly was a popular American print magazine dedicated to geek culture, published from 2006 to 2010. It provided an exciting mix of content on diverse topics such as video games, comic books, technology, and popular science. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Founding and Publication History ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Fueled by the rising interest in geek culture in the 21st century, the publication was launched in 2006 by CFQ Media, an entity known earlier for the science fiction and horror film magazine, Cinefantastique. Geek Monthly gained traction among enthusiasts for its accurate, in-depth, and user-friendly presentation of geek-related content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content and Coverage ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Geek Monthly offered a compelling mix of content across various facets of geek culture. It provided reviews of emerging tech gadgets, previews and reviews of video games, updates on comic book releases, and coverage of the science fiction genre across various media. Apart from these, Geek Monthly also spotlighted the more serious side of geek culture, incorporating discussions about science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Geek Monthly''s coverage of entertainment included insightful interviews with celebrities relevant to the geek culture, including writers, movie creators, and television stars. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Transition to Digital' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In 2010, Geek Monthly ceased its print operations, transitioning to a digital-only format under the website name GeekExchange.com. The switch reflected the increasing digital consumption of media content, especially within the demographic niche Geek Monthly catered to. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'While the print version of Geek Monthly no longer exists, its digital avatar continues to entertain and inform a dedicated audience, serving as a testament to the evolution of media consumption and the enduring appeal of geek culture.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The General Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The General Magazine', N'the-general-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription American bi-monthly gaming magazine (1964-1998) focused on strategy board games, gameplay advice, and historical context.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'# The General' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The General was an American bi-monthly gaming magazine published by the Avalon Hill game company. It focused on the company''s strategy board games with an emphasis on play details, historical context, and strategic advice.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'First published in 1964, The General was tailored specifically as a house organ to promote Avalon Hill''s wargames. It served this role efficiently for 32 years until its final issue was published in 1998.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content and Purpose' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine comprised specialized content catering to the specific interests of strategic wargame enthusiasts. Regular inclusions in each issue were historical analyses pertinent to Avalon Hill games, replays of games providing detailed insights into gameplay, and articles offering a variety of strategic and tactical advice.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The General didn''t just focus on offering gameplay tips; often it would delve into the historical context of the conflict being simulated, broadening players'' understanding of the actual events behind the games.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Special Features' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Peculiar to The General was its inclusion of variant rules and new scenarios for Avalon Hill games. These amendments were proposed either by staff writers or submitted by readers, offering fresh perspectives and challenges to keep the gameplay experience stimulating.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Another regular feature was ''The Avalon Hill Philosophy'', a column written by Avalon Hill''s founder, Charles Roberts, in which he would discuss his views on wargaming and game design.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Transition and Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The advent of the digital age saw a decline in readership which eventually led to The General''s termination in 1998. Despite this, the magazine''s influence persisted. The contributions it made to wargaming went beyond its original purpose, creating a rich legacy that advanced the state of strategic board gaming to new heights.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- The Genesee Farmer
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'The Genesee Farmer', N'the-genesee-farmer', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription 19th-century American agricultural periodical disseminating farming techniques, scientific research, and rural domestic affairs.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'# The Genesee Farmer' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Genesee Farmer was a 19th-century American agricultural periodical based in Rochester, New York. It catered to the interests of the farming community, disseminating information on agriculture, horticulture, and associated domestic and rural affairs.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was first launched in 1831 by Luther Tucker, a prominent publisher of agricultural magazines. The Genesee Farmer was initially issued as a monthly digest, and over the course of its history changed its publication frequency several times in response to the demands and interests of its readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content and Purpose' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Similar to many agricultural publications of the time, The Genesee Farmer was devoted to the improvement and prosperity of the farming community. Its content often blended practical farming advice with scientific knowledge, presenting research in agronomy, botany, and other closely related fields in an understandable and applicable manner for farmers.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Format and Sections' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The periodical was formatted for convenient reading and ease of reference, featuring distinct sections such as Crop Reports, Farm Management, Horticultural Techniques, and Household Management, among others. Readers could participate by writing letters to the editor, sharing farming experiences, techniques, or queries, which fostered a sense of community and exchange among its readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Genesee Farmer offered crucial insights into 19th-century American agriculture and rural life and was a significant platform for the sharing and propagation of farming techniques and scientific knowledge. Its influence extended far beyond its core audience, helping to shape American agriculture''s practices and methods during a critical period of growth and technological advancement.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Genre Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Genre Magazine', N'genre-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription U.S.-based monthly LGBT lifestyle and culture periodical published between 1992 and 2009.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Genre Magazine' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Genre Magazine was a U.S.-based monthly periodical aimed at the LGBT community, focusing on lifestyle, fashion, travel, and entertainment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Publication History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Genre Magazine was first issued in 1992, entering the market as a publication addressing the lifestyle and cultural interests of the gay community. The magazine thrived for more than a decade, gaining a significant readership across the United States. However, it faced financial challenges in the wake of the 2008 economic crisis and ceased publication in 2009.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Content and Coverage' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s content featured a mix of lifestyle, travel, fashion, and entertainment, along with regular discussions on important social, political, and health issues affecting the gay community. It presented its readers with inspiring stories of success from within the LGBT community and aimed to challenge stereotypes while promoting acceptance and equality.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Format and Design' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine was known for its avant-garde design and high-quality print. The stunning visual presentation and sharp, innovative layouts were distinguishing features that captured the attention of its target readership.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Pioneering Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Though no longer in circulation, Genre Magazine is considered a pioneering publication for its inclusive coverage and contributions to the LGBT community. At the time of its publication, it profoundly impacted the visibility and representation of LGBT individuals. By discussing a wide variety of lifestyle topics, it played a crucial role in normalizing and promoting LGBT lifestyles in mainstream society.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Gent Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
