VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly Spanish-language magazine based in the United States focusing on culture, entertainment, fashion, and current events targeted at bilingual and bicultural Hispanics.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H magazine is a monthly publication that features articles and photographs about current events, entertainment, fashion, and culture. Published since 1998, the magazine is one of the leading Spanish-language publications in the United States.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H magazine was founded in 1998 by Televisa Publishing International, a subsidiary of Grupo Televisa, the largest Spanish-language media company in the world. The magazine was launched to target young, bilingual, and bicultural Hispanics living in the United States.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s first editor-in-chief was Juan Santamaria, who served in that position until 2001 when he was replaced by Jose Antonio Evora, who remained at the helm until 2004.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H magazine features a mix of celebrity interviews, lifestyle articles, and fashion spreads, as well as news and opinion pieces on current events and politics. The magazine also includes sections on beauty, health, and travel.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Since 2011, the magazine has been published in a digital format, offering readers an online platform to access content.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Influence' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H magazine is influential in the Hispanic community, particularly among young, bicultural and bilingual readers. The magazine has been praised for its coverage of important issues affecting the Hispanic community, such as immigration and social justice.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine has also been recognized for supporting emerging Latino artists and musicians, providing a platform for up-and-coming talent on the Hispanic entertainment scene.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Awards and Recognition' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H magazine has received numerous awards and accolades for its work over the years. In 2004, the magazine won the National Association of Hispanic Publications Award for Best Magazine for its coverage of the September 11 attacks.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine has also received recognition for its coverage of the Latin Grammy Awards, including a nomination for Best National Publication in 2015.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "H Magazine." Telemundo. Created on 12 December 2009, Accessed 1 August 2023. https://www.telemundo52.com/especiales/5-cosas-que-no-sabias-sobre-la-revista-h/1860229/.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "About H Magazine." H Magazine. Accessed 1 August 2023. https://www.hmagazine.com/about-us/.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- H. P. Lovecraft's Magazine of Horror
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'H. P. Lovecraft''s Magazine of Horror', N'h-p-lovecrafts-magazine-of-horror', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A bi-monthly horror fiction and literature magazine published in the United States between 1979 and 1985, aimed at showcasing new authors and promoting the horror fiction genre.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H. P. Lovecraft''s Magazine of Horror was a bi-monthly publication dedicated to horror fiction and related topics, published in the United States between 1979 and 1985. The magazine was named after H. P. Lovecraft, a prominent author of horror fiction in the early 20th century.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H. P. Lovecraft''s Magazine of Horror was first published in 1979 by George H. Scithers, Darrell Schweitzer, and John M. Ford. The magazine was published out of Philadelphia and aimed to publish high-quality horror fiction, scholarship, and criticism.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The first issue included stories by well-known authors such as Ramsey Campbell, Thomas Ligotti, and Manly Wade Wellman. In addition to stories, the magazine also published reviews, interviews, and essays on horror literature and related topics.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'H. P. Lovecraft''s Magazine of Horror published a wide variety of horror fiction, ranging from traditional ghost stories to modern psychological thrillers. In addition to fiction, the magazine also published non-fiction articles on horror literature and related topics. ' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the magazine''s recurring features was "The Eyrie," a letters column which included commentary on horror literature and fan culture, as well as responses from the editorial team.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although H. P. Lovecraft''s Magazine of Horror was only published for six years, it had a significant impact on horror literature and fan culture. The magazine helped to revive interest in horror fiction and played a role in the emergence of the "weird fiction" subgenre.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also provided a platform for new authors to showcase their work, including some who went on to achieve significant acclaim in the horror and fantasy genres.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- Schweitzer, Darrell. "H.P. Lovecraft''s Magazine of Horror." Encyclopedia of Fantasy, edited by John Clute and John Grant, Orbit Books, 1997, p. 477.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- Lovecraft, H. P. The Complete Fiction of H. P. Lovecraft, edited by S.T. Joshi, Barnes & Noble, Inc., 2008, pp. 995-996.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Ham Radio Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Ham Radio Magazine', N'ham-radio-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly publication catering to amateur radio enthusiasts in the United States, featuring technical aspects, news and opinions, construction projects, and equipment reviews.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ham Radio magazine was a monthly publication established in 1968 to serve amateur radio enthusiasts in the United States. The magazine was dedicated to the technical and practical aspects of amateur radio communication, as well as news and opinions related to the hobby.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ham Radio magazine was first published in June 1968 by Wayne Green, W2NSD. The magazine was published out of a small office in New Hampshire, with Green serving as editor and publisher.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine primarily focused on technical aspects of amateur radio, including construction projects, antenna design, and equipment reviews. However, it also included news and opinion pieces related to the amateur radio community, including regulatory and legal issues.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ham Radio magazine''s content was divided into several sections, including features, construction projects, equipment reviews, and letters to the editor. The magazine also featured a regular column titled "Never Say Die," which focused on troubleshooting and problem-solving in amateur radio communications.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Throughout its history, the magazine included interviews with prominent figures in the amateur radio community, as well as coverage of major events and contests in the hobby.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Ham Radio magazine played an important role in the growth and development of the amateur radio hobby in the United States. The magazine helped to spread knowledge and information about the technical aspects of amateur radio, and provided a platform for enthusiasts to share their experiences and opinions.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine also helped to build a sense of community among amateur radio operators, by providing a forum for discussion and debate about the hobby and its future.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- Green, Wayne. "Ham Radio." 73 Magazine, October 1970, pp. 70-76.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "Ham Radio Magazine." QST, August 1968, p. 102.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Hands-On Electronics
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Hands-On Electronics', N'hands-on-electronics', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A monthly magazine providing practical advice and tutorials for building and repairing electronic devices, as well as news and opinions related to the electronics industry.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics was a monthly magazine dedicated to the practical aspects of electronics. The magazine provided readers with tips and tutorials for building and repairing electronic devices, as well as news and opinions related to the electronics industry.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics was first published in 1983 by Gernsback Publications. The magazine was aimed at electronics enthusiasts and professionals, providing practical advice for building and repairing electronic devices.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Hands-On Electronics published articles on a wide range of topics, including audio amplifiers, digital circuits, microcontrollers, and more. The magazine also featured detailed construction projects, complete with circuit diagrams and parts lists.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Despite its focus on practical electronics, the magazine also included news and opinion pieces related to the electronics industry, as well as interviews with prominent figures in the field.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics'' content was divided into several sections, including features, projects, news, and opinion pieces. The magazine also included a regular column titled "Electronics Q&A," which provided readers with answers to common questions about electronic devices and circuits.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The magazine''s construction projects were a major focus, often featuring detailed instructions and diagrams for building everything from simple gadgets to complex audio systems. The magazine also included equipment reviews, helping readers to make informed decisions about purchasing electronic equipment.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hands-On Electronics played an important role in the growth and development of the electronics industry, providing readers with practical advice and tutorials for building and repairing electronic devices. The magazine helped to build a sense of community among electronics enthusiasts, and provided a platform for sharing knowledge and ideas.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although the magazine is no longer in publication, its legacy lives on through the many practical projects and tutorials that it published over the years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- Vagnoni, Anthony. "Hands-On Electronics Magazine: An Overview." Electronic Design, 24 Oct. 1994, www.electronicdesign.com/technologies/test-measurement/article/21774467/handson-electronics-magazine-an-overview.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "Hands-On Electronics Magazine." WorldCat, www.worldcat.org/title/hands-on-electronics-magazine/oclc/18337606.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

-- Hardgainer Magazine
INSERT Articles (Title, UrlSlug, SiteId, Culture)
VALUES ( N'Hardgainer Magazine', N'hardgainer-magazine', 1, 'en' );
INSERT ArticleRevisions (ArticleId, [Text], RevisionReason, CreatedByAspNetUserId)
VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A Bi-Monthly magazine providing practical advice on strength training and bodybuilding for individuals who struggle to gain muscle mass.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer was a bi-monthly magazine focused on strength training and bodybuilding for individuals naturally prone to difficulty in gaining muscle mass, called "hardgainers". The magazine was known for its practical advice and emphasis on progressive overload training principles.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer was founded in 1989 by Stuart McRobert, an author and bodybuilder who wrote extensively on the subject of strength training. The magazine quickly gained a following among individuals who struggled to gain muscle mass, offering practical advice for building strength and size.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Over the years, Hardgainer published articles on a wide range of topics related to strength training and bodybuilding, including training routines, nutrition, and supplementation. The magazine also emphasized the importance of progress tracking and the use of free weights in workouts.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Content' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer''s content was divided into several sections, including training, nutrition, and supplementation. The magazine''s training section included workout routines and tips for building strength and muscle mass.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The nutrition section focused on providing practical advice for individuals with fast metabolisms or digestive issues, ensuring that they were able to consume enough nutrients to support muscle growth. The magazine also provided supplement recommendations, but emphasized that supplements are not a substitute for proper nutrition.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'One of the magazine''s recurring features was the "Hardgainer Q&A," which answered reader-submitted questions related to training, nutrition, and supplementation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Hardgainer played an important role in the bodybuilding and fitness industry, providing practical advice for individuals who had difficulty gaining muscle mass. The magazine emphasized the importance of progressive overload training principles and tracking progress, two concepts that are still highly regarded in the fitness community today.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'Although the magazine is no longer in publication, its legacy lives on through the many practical training tips and principles that it espoused over the years.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## References' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- McRobert, Stuart. "Hardgainer magazine: the story, philosophy and practical wisdom of the original Hardgainer." Haverford, PA: CS Publishing Ltd., 2019.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'- "Hardgainer Magazine." WorldCat, www.worldcat.org/title/hardgainer-magazine/oclc/25944533.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

