VALUES (SCOPE_IDENTITY(), N'{{ShortDescription A 19th-century American monthly magazine focused on gardening and horticulture, known for its high-quality articles and illustrations.}}' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Introduction' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Horticulturist was a monthly magazine that focused on gardening and horticulture. Originally published in the United States in the mid-19th century, the magazine was known for its high-quality articles and illustrations.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## History' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Horticulturist was founded in 1846 by horticulturist and author P. Barry. The magazine was published in New York and was priced at $3 per year.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Horticulturist became known for its high-quality articles and illustrations, which covered a wide range of topics related to gardening and horticulture. The magazine also provided information on new varieties of plants and seeds, and offered advice on garden design and cultivation.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its high-quality content, The Horticulturist also became known for its distinctive layout and design. The magazine featured a mix of text and illustrations, with color plates and engravings interspersed throughout its pages.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Horticulturist continued to publish for nearly four decades, until it ceased publication in 1881.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Style' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Horticulturist was known for its high-quality articles and illustrations, which were written and produced by leading horticulturists and garden designers of the period. The magazine''s content covered a wide range of topics related to gardening and horticulture, including plant cultivation, garden design, and landscape architecture.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its informative content, The Horticulturist was prized for its high-quality illustrations and prints. The magazine employed skilled artists and engravers to produce color plates and engravings that captured the beauty and diversity of the natural world.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'## Legacy' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'The Horticulturist had a significant impact on the development of gardening and horticulture in the United States. The magazine helped to popularize gardening as a pastime and a profession, and provided a valuable resource for garden enthusiasts and professionals alike.' + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + CHAR(13) + CHAR(10) + N'In addition to its impact on gardening and horticulture, The Horticulturist also helped to establish the tradition of illustrated magazines in the United States. The magazine''s distinctive layout and design influenced the development of other illustrated periodicals of the period, and helped to establish the importance of high-quality printing and illustration in American publishing.{{Categories Magazines}}', N'Article created.', '7240be61-df81-46f9-8152-6a48b96abc40');

